Furnaces require compressed cobblestone (72x cobblestone). Smelt some Wood Logs using any soil fuel to create charcoal.

Punching trees and gravel blocks with your fists will give you the first materials you need to start your journey.

Crafting Table will allow you to craft 3x3 recipes.

Mortar and pestle is used to craft flint from gravel. Flint does NOT drop from gravel in this pack.


§aThen choose your reward... a Shovel for quickly gathering sand, gravel, and clay; or an Axe for quickly cutting down trees. There are no wrong answers!

Stencil Table: Converts blank patterns to tool patterns.

Part Builder: Crafts tool parts using patterns and materials.

Tool Station: Crafts tools using tool parts, repairs, and upgrades tools.


Craft some blank patterns and shape them into the required tool parts in the stencil table.

The flint pickaxe is the most basic pickaxe you can make.

When a Tinker's Construct tool breaks, you can repair it with the main material (in this case flint) in a 2x2 crafting grid.

Keep mining Stone with it until it gets boosted to be able to mine coal, salt, copper, and aluminum ore. Pickaxes can only be boosted once. In order to mine other ores, you are going to need to make a more durable pickaxe later down the road.

Kill some skeletons and create a sword out of its bones. Then turn in the sword to me and i'll reward you with a better weapon.

- All parts of the sword must be made out of bones (Hold Control while hovering over the sword to see the parts needed).
- The sword must be fully repaired.
- The sword must be named "Bill".
- The sword must be brand new and never used before.


With a sword in one hand, what can you do with the other? Right, you need a shield. Let's make one.

All these ingredients will create a 5x5x3 smeltery (3x3x2 inside) with 2x drains.

Look at YouTube or Google search for a guide on how to build this stucture.


The mailbox reward allows you to send and receive mail between all players on the server who have placed a mailbox down. You can access your own mail from ANY mailbox in the world. You will get a notification on the top of your screen when you recieve mail. Letters require stamps.
-

Combine 3x aluminum ore and 1x copper ore in the smeltery to melt and combine the metals into molten aluminum-brass.

Place a tool part on the casting table (such as a flint pickaxe head) and right-click the faucet to pour the molten aluminum-brass onto the tool part. The tool part will burn away and you will be left with a new metal cast that you can pour metals into to make metal tool parts.

Use a Brick to create an Ingot Cast.

Make a copper pickaxe head and whatever type of binding and rod. This is your next tool upgrade.

You may now retire you Flint Pickaxe.


The FluiVac is capable of pulling fluids from the world and storing them in items in your inventory that can store fluids. It can also take fluids from your inventory and place the fluid in the world or into blocks in the world.

The FluiVac can be toggled between input and output mode by pressing the C key (default) while holding it.

Craft an Iron Pickaxe. Only the pickaxe head needs to be iron. The other 2 parts can be made out of any other material.

You may now retire your Copper Pickaxe.

Craft a Bronze Pickaxe after combining copper ore and tin ore in the smeltery.

You may now retire your Iron Pickaxe.

After you create a blast furnace, create some steel ingots and melt them down in a smeltery. 

Make a Steel Pickaxe and you may now retire your Bronze Pickaxe.

Once you boosted your pickaxe to mine obsidian, melt down iron, aluminum, and obsidian in a smetery to create alumite alloy.

Create an Alumite Pickaxe and you may now retire your Steel Pickaxe.

The Blast Furnace is a multiblock structure used to convert Iron to Steel. The Blast Furnace accepts only two types of fuel: Charcoal or Coal Coke.

- The oven is built out of 34 Blast Furnace Bricks (3 wide, 3 deep, 4 high).
- Base and top layers: 3x3.
- Middle two layers: 3x3 with hollow center.

Coke oven is a multi-block structure that cooks coal into coal coke with creosote as a bi-product. It does not require fuel to run; however, it takes much longer then a normal furnace.

Wood logs can also be used to make charcoal and a small amount of creosote.


Your reward for completing this is a Wrench which can be used to rotate and pick up many tile entities.

Travel to The Nether and mine up some ardite ore then melt it down into an Aridite Pickaxe.

You may now retire your Alumite Pickaxe.
Mixing cobalt and ardite in a smeltery will create manyullyu. It is one of the strongest materials in the game and the only material that can mine draconium ore (once it's boosted).

Find a stronghold in the world by throwing eyes of ender into the air and following them. Fill up the portal with eyes of ender and travel to The End.

The Enchantment Table allows you to spend your experience point to enchant (non-Tinker's Construct) tools, books and armor.

The Anvil allows you to spend your experience points and material to fix up your (non-TConstruct) tools and armor.


§aPick your new girlfriend as a reward!
How can you be so careless?

The Assemby Table is used to make chipsets that are used everywhere in the electrical age. The Lasers are partnered with the table (usually placed below the lasers) to send the power to the table. They must be placed within 4-blocks of the table. The lasers require power while the table does not.

Items produced by the Assembly Table will pop out into the world and may despawn. If there is an adjacent inventory to the Assembly Table, produced items will be placed into it instead.

The Clockwork Engine is an early-game RF generating engine that does not need any fuel. To power the engine, you have to hold right-click to wind the engine up. The engine will generate power after it is wound for a short duriation before you have to wind it again. There is no way to automate this engine.

Do not wind the engine for too long in one-go, it might fight back.

The redstone engines you get as a reward do not produce RF. They are used to pump items out of buildcraft pipes.
Basic Machine Frames are used everywhere in the electric age. I highly recommend you automate the production of them and the chipsets you created in the quest above.

The Hobbyist's Steam engine is a stand alone engine, capable of running on its own as long as you supply it with enough fuel and water, and a redstone signal. The water inside will boil once the temperature of the engine is at or exceeds 100 degrees.

To keep the Hobbyist's Steam engine from eventually overheating, it is possible to use an Aqueous Accumulator. 

If your engine runs out of water but still has fuel burned, make sure you shut off the power and let it cool otherwise it will explode when you try adding more water to it.
If you make your tools out of Pig Iron, there is a small chance that the tool will drop Bacon Strips during normal use. This is useful because... well... think about it.

Mixing metals is a large part of creating more complicated machines and upgrades later down the road. Some of the more common alloys are listed below. Melting down different metals in a smeltery will mix them together if they are able to.

Bronze:
3x Copper + 1x Tin

Invar:
2x Nickel + 1x Iron

Electrum:
1x Gold + 1x Silver

I need to make sure you are ready to enter the machine age before you actually get there. If you jump in without being prepaired, there may be some fustration before you even make your first machine.

There are a decent amount of materials needed to make a binding material called Grog, It is used to make circuits that are used in majority of machines. Make sure you have a good supply of all these materials before you start building machines.

- Brown mushrooms can be grown in the dark.
- Sludge can be found around the Overworld in small pools on the surface.

The Compartment is a chest which contain several tabs to help organise their contents. Each tab can be named, assigned a color and assigned an icon from any item. The number of tabs and size of each page depends on the material used to construct the chest.

Repeatable - 1 Day
Just click the checkbox to get yourself $50 in cold, hard, cash.


§oSo easy a caveman can do it...
It's my money and I need it now!

Jetpacks consume RF and allow the user to fly. The Leadstone Jetpack is the first method of flight available; however, going straight for a Hardened Jetpack is probably your best bet. You can install Armor Plating on Jetpacks to give them some chest protection. Higher tiers of Jetpack can have higher tiers of Armor Plating.

Keyboard 'J' by default to open the jetpack menu to be able to:
- Turn on/off the jetpack itself.
- Turn on/off hover mode.
- Turn on/off the built-in charger (high tiers only).

Conveyor Belts are used as a means of transporting items, mobs, and players. A wrench can be used to modify the direction of the conveyor belt including diagonal vertical movement (e.g. creating escalators).

One important aspect of Conveyor Belts is that anything being transported on it will stick to the belt, including when intersecting belts that turn, but will fall off if the belt ends abruptly at a vertical fall. This makes them useful when setting up mob farms, especially when combined with an Auto-Spawner or Soul Cage and a Grinder.

To move items from a conveyor belt into a chest, an Item Collector is needed. Belts can be sped up by right-clicking on them with Glowstone. Belts will not move the player if they are wearing Plastic Boots.

One way to shorten travel time is to create a railroad from your base to the different areas around the map. Sadly this requires a large amount of both iron and creosote. Let's not forget to place the last symbolic rivet on one of your new train lines.

If connecting your railroad to the main line (the one connecting spawn to the rest of the map). Please read more information in the Rules/Laws questline to determine how to do that properly.

Hover Upgrade
Allows the jetpack to be switched to hover mode. Installing more than one has no effect.

Flight Speed Control Upgrade
Increases the speed at which the player flies by 0.4 m/s for each item installed.

Atmosphere Analyzer	
A display in the lwer left hand corner of the screen displaying current atmosphere and breathability will be shown. The same information can be displayed if the item is right clicked in the world

Anti-Fog Visor
Easily see through the fog on high pressure planets.

Beacon Finder
Display arrows at the top of the screen pointing to active beacons on the same planet.

Chests hold items... If you really needed me to tell you that, you probably shouldn't be playing this pack.

Slightly Larger Chest takes up an entire 1x1x1 block space. This is useful for hiding pipes or machines behind it.

This backpack holds the same amount as a Satchel with holding 1; however, it can be upgraded and configured with tons of upgrades.

This requires a tier 1 satchel with the "Holding 1" enchant on it.

Repeatable - 1 Day

$1,000 to buy a Knapsack that goes into your Tinkers' Construct player inventory (Diamond Chestplate tab at the top). It gives you another single chest's worth of items you can access anytime you are alive.

Buildcraft tanks each can hold 16 buckets of liquid each and can be stacked vertically to increase the overall capacity. Tanks will NOT connect when placed adjacent to each other.

These tanks will lose all their stored liquid when broken.

Reapeatable - 2 hours
$200 for a Saddle you can use to mount Horses and Pigs.

Railcraft tank is an expandable multi-block structure that holds a large amount of liquid. Valid dimensions are 3x3, 5x5, 7x7 or 9x9, from 4 up to 8 blocks tall. Railcraft tanks can hold 16 buckets of liquid for each block in the structure.

The frame of a Railcraft Tank must be constructed of Tank Walls. The inside must be empty and the walls may be filled in with any of the tank blocks. Valves allow the tank to interact with other machines and pipes. The tank will form into a single structure once all the outer walls are complete, and nothing is inside.

Railcraft tanks made out of steel hold 32 buckets of liquid for each block instead of iron's 16 buckets.

The materials to the right are everything you need to make the biggest and densest railcraft tank.

Storage Drawers can hold a large amount of a single item type.

Right-Click: Insert full stack in hand into drawer (or partial stack if the drawer fills).
Double-Right-Click: Insert all compatible stacks in inventory into drawer (or until drawer fills).
Left-Click: Remove a single item from the drawer.
Shift+Left-Click: Remove a full stack from the drawer.
Shift+Right-Click with empty hand: Open a UI to see exact item counts and manage applied upgrades.

The total storage of the drawers are divided evenly between each slot of the drawers. Each (non-upgraded) slot can hold 32 stacks of items total divided by the amount of slots.

Iron Chests are better than vanilla chests in that they have more capacity and can be placed next to each other. Additionally, they remain as single chests when adjacent to each other, eliminating the necessary 1-block gap seen with double chests.

Copper Chest:
Capacity: 45 Inventory slots

The Matter Transmitter is a block added by RFTools. It is a transportation device that can send a player across space and dimensions to a specified Matter Receiver. It must be used in conjunction with a Dialing Device. When successfully dialed to a receiver, the transmitter will project a 3-block high teleportation beam. By stepping into the beam, the player is transmitted to the destination.
Yellow Hearts can be obtained by killing Boss type mobs such as the Wither or King Slime, as well as from killing any size of Blue Slime. 5 hearts drop from the death of the Ender Dragon.

Ender Chests have three wool pads on top that can be manipulated by right-clicking them with a dye. All Ender Chests with the same 3-color code will access a shared inventory, no matter what dimension they are placed in.

For example, a white-orange-yellow Ender Chest shares its inventory with all other red-orange-yellow Ender Chests, but cannot be accessed at a red-yellow-orange Ender Chest. There are 4,096 possible 3-color codes.

If the player right-clicks the latch of an Ender Chest with a diamond, it will no longer connect to Ender Chests of the same color code, except those which that same player has also diamond-locked.

For example, if TheOnlyRupert diamond-locks a red-red-red Ender Chest, that chest will now only connect to other red-red-red Ender Chests that TheOnlyRupert has diamond-locked.


§aBe sure to check the pined message in Discord to check the claimed colors of everyone in the server. To claim your own color, visit the Town Hall and put in an §nEnder Chest Color Request§r§a.

Ender Tanks work similar to Ender Chests, but for fluids. They are color coded by right-clicking the 3 wool bits at the top, and can be set to be specifically for your player by right-clicking the center bit with a diamond.

Multiple tanks with the exact same color coordination and diamond share the same fluid inventory, so you can put one at, say, a lava pump in the Nether and put another next to your Smeltery.

Right click on the center-front bit to change it from input to output.


§aBe sure to check the pined message in Discord to check the claimed colors of everyone in the server. To claim your own color, visit the Town Hall and put in an §nEnder Chest Color Request§r§a.

An Ender Chest / Ender Pouch combo is great for moving items from your inventory back to your base. For instance, while Mining, you can put Ores into the Pouch, and then have the Ores sucked out of the Ender Chest into your storage or processing.

You can right-click a diamond onto the chest jewel thing that pops out of the front to set it to your player. That way, a diamond white-white-white is different than the regular white-white-white. Shift-right-click the Ender Chest with the Ender Pouch to link to two.


§aBe sure to check the pined message in Discord to check the claimed colors of everyone in the server. To claim your own color, visit the Town Hall and put in an §nEnder Chest Color Request§r§a.

Hopefully you still have that free portable tank I gave you. You might as well upgrade it all the way to the max tier. Like the buildcraft and open blocks tanks, you can stack these on top of each other to join the liquids.

Right-click with a wrench to change the mode between input/output.

Portable Tank:
Capacity: 8 Buckets of liquid

Hardened Portable Tank:
Capacity: 32 Buckets of liquid

Capacity: 128 Buckets of liquid

Capacity: 512 Buckets of liquid

Builder's Wand is used to place blocks by right-clicking on a side of the same block. The Iron Wand can place a total of 9 blocks per right-click.

Builder's Wands can be enchanted.

§nModes:§r (change modes with Comma key)
- Horizontal: Extend left and right from the original block. No building on top/bottom face.
- Vertical: Extend up and down from the original block. No building on top/bottom face.

The Cyclic Assembler is an automated Crafting Table which produces items from a recipe stored on a Schematic.

To use it, place a Schematic in the appropriate slot and the recipe on it will be crafted given all items needed are in the Assembler's inventory or piped in. A blank Schematic may be encoded with a recipe using the grid in the blue Schematic tab (right-hand side of the GUI), pressing the check mark will encode the pattern on the Schematic. This Schematic may be stored to use at a later time when the item is needed.

If a recipe calls for a container of liquid, it may also be piped directly into the internal tank instead of supplying the containers.
The Glacial Precipitator is used to produce Snow, Ice and Snowballs from Water. It has an internal buffer to hold 32 buckets of water.

Phytogenic Insolator is used to generate crops without the regular farming process. Using the respective seeds, Phyto-Gro (or Rich Phyto-Gro) fertilizer, water, and some power will grow the crop within the machine itself.
The Knowledge Inscriber works similar to the Pattern Terminal; however, instead of Patterns, you use a Knowledge Core. Each Core can store 21 recipes on it.

The Filler is a machine that will "fill" a specified area with all blocks or with a specifically chosen design. It can also clear an area of all blocks. One of six patterns are designated for the Filler to determine what to do with the specified area.

An area to be filled must be specified using Land Marks. At least four Land Marks must be used to specify a three-dimensional area for the Filler to work in. Right-click the Land Marks to create a red frame of the area, then place the Filler at one of the Land Marks. The Land Marks will pop out of the ground and a black and yellow frame will show the designated area.

Fill - Fill entire area with blocks.
Flatten - Clears all blocks from the area, clears all blocks above it, and fills in open holes directly beneath it with blocks.
Frame - 
Horizon - 
Pyramid - Creates a Pyramid in the area
Stairs - Creates a Staircase in the area
Box - Creates box in the area.
Clear - Clear entire area.
Cylinder - Creates a Cylinder in the area

Put seeds into the Seed Analyzer to convert the seed to an Agricraft seed and to see its current statistics.

Seeds have 3 statistics:
Growth - how fast the crop matures
Gain - how much you get from a single crop
Strength - resilience to weeds and ability to move with clippers.

The Mining Well will dig a 1x1 hole straight down underneath it. It will stop drilling down once it hits lava or bedrock. 

EXPERT: Try connecting lots of mining wells to a moving platform to collect ores.

The grindstone block is a manual way of turning items into dusts and even doubling your output chance from ores.

Place the crank on the top of the machine and hold right-click to turn the crank and start crushing materials. If there is nothing in the machine, the crank will not turn and it will eventually break off.

It takes 24 real life hours to turn one seed into a pure crystal. This stuff will be used MUCH later in the pack; however, you might as well get the hard part out of the way first.

Make as many as you're comfortable with right now, because you'll need them later. Throw them in water and just wait.

MFR's Wrench can be used as a standard wrench in most cases. When the wrench is held the area of effect of all placed MFR machines are shown by transparent, colored boxes. If any upgrades have been added, this is reflected by the size of the area.


§aBe careful where you plant that Mega Rubber Tree Sapling. The tree is just a little bit big!

- Silky Jewel will make a tool mine the extact block in the world.
- Lava Crystal will make a tool cook the block first before mining.
- Redstone will make a tool mine faster.
- Lapis will add a greater drop rate of blocks mined.
- Quartz will make tool hurt more when attacking.

Pulverisor smashed down materials into their dust form.

Pulverisors double the output amount of ore output with a small chance of giving a secondary byproduct as a result.

Rock crusher, crushes materials into crushed versions of itself.

This machine is different then a pulverisor because it crushes materials instead of turning it to dust,

Ore -> Rock Crusher -> Pulverisor -> Smelter -> Ingot -> Gives a 3x ore output.
Redstone furnace is the same thing as a regular furnace; however, it takes RF power instead of burning fuel direcly in the machine.

This block needs water blocks touching at least 2 sides of the machine for it to generate water for free. It will fill up with 4x buckets of water that can be pumped out with pipes.

This machine does not accept power.
This machine will give 4x output of wood logs -> wood planks. It also gives sawdust as an output.
Induction Smeltery is mainly used for turning dusts into ingots quickly, It is also used to combine metals or materials into mixed versions much faster than a Tinker's Construct smeltery.
Infuser is mainly used to store energy that can quickly charge tools and weapons that need power to operate.

This ignious extruder is used to generate blocks that are made from combining water and lava. The machine needs at least one bucket of water and lava in the machine for it to work.

Generates cobblestone for free.
Generates smooth stone using 1x bucket of water for each operation.
Generates obsidian using 1x bucket of water and 1x bucket of lava for each operation.

This machine does not accept power.

Stores power for later use.

Upgrade the leadstone energy cell to hardened energy cell.
Redstone energy cell stores a lot more energy.

This is a multi-block structure intended for storing absurdly large amounts of RF energy. It is built pretty much exactly the same way as a Big Reactor, with minor differences.

Sulfuric Acid creation:
- Dig a 3x3 hole and place a Block of Sulfur in the middle block.
- Fill the remaining 8 blocks with Water and set fire to the Block of Sulfur.
- After a while the water will convert to liquid sulfur.

The Rocket Assembling Machine is a multiblock structure that will allow you to make Rockets to go into space. This quest will only detail how to build the structure.

Start by placing Launch Pad blocks in a rectangle on the ground. It can be anywhere from 3x3 to 16x16. On the same level, place a Structure Tower near one of the side, then stack up more of them to make a 1 block tower. This tower can be anywhere from 4 to 64 blocks tall.

Finally, place the Rocket Assembling Machine itself one block above the level of the Pads, with the back of the machine facing the Pad, and plug it with RF. If you did this correctly, it should no longer say "Invalid Launch Pad Structure".

Then you need the Fueling Station to be able to fuel your Rockets. Place it somewhere near the Assembling Machine, plug it with RF and your source of Rocket Fuel, then shift+right-click it with a Linker, then shift+right-click the Assembling Machine with the same Linker.

Tired of your stuff falling out of your crafting table every time you walk away?  This fancy table will hold the items in your recipe. 

You can also place it next to a tool station or tool forge to upgrade with 8 modifiers at a time. Very handy for additional speed or looting. When it is placed next to a vanilla chest, it will show the chest's inventory.


Portable Crafting Table is a tool that allows you to craft in a 3x3 grid without having to walk to a crafting table. Simple pressing C (by default) will open the table for quick and easy crafting.
Same as Chest Transporter (Basic) with much higher durability.

The Sprinkler distributes water from an irrigation system to keep the surrounding area hydrated and increase the growth rate of crops within the 7×7 area. Its vertical reach is 5m for irrigating and 4m for growth acceleration.

To be effective, the Sprinkler needs a water supply from a Wood Water Tank gravity fed with a Wood Irrigation Channel. Place the Sprinkler under the Channel to start hydrating the crops below. The Tank can be refilled using a Pump or an Aqueous Accumulator and a liquid transport system such as Fluiduct.

Regular vanilla farming mechanics still work; however, there is not a guarentee that the mature plant will even drop the product when it is harvested. To guarentee the drop, you have to use crop sticks and read up on how to use the Agricraft mod.

Crop Sticks are where you plant seeds to grow them the AgriCraft way. If you right-click a valid soil block with them, it will plant the sticks and allow you to plant seeds in it. Plants growing on these can be harvested by right-clicking instead of breaking. If you right-click Crop Sticks with Crop Sticks, you will put even more on, which allows you to crossbreed crops that are touching it. For instance, if you put 2 Crop Sticks onto soil between Carrots with 1x1x1 stats (assuming that they're on single Crop Sticks), there will be a chance that they will crossbreed and upgrade into 2x2x2 stats.

Cross-breading into new crops is disabled. To find new crops you need to hoe the ground, find them in villages, or harvest them from gardens around the world.

To combine two different crops or spread the growth of a single crop, placing a crop stick on appropriate farm land and then placing a second one on top will cause the crops to cross each other. Nearby plants will attempt to grow to this cross crop and there is a small chance the plants will crossbreed into a new plant.

The Veterinary Station is used to apply syringes to animals in a 5×5 area in front of the Station.

1: Health Syringes heal animals by a small amount.
2: Growth Syringes turn baby animals and villagers into adults.
3: Zombie Syringes have a chance to either turn the baby into an adult or a Zombie.
4: Slime Embiggening Syringes can also be used by the Veterinary Station to grow Slime.

You are required to:

- Automate Letter and Tier 5 Stamp creation.
- Automatically turn in 1,000 Letters and Stamps.

You are required to:

- Automate Bee(s) of your choice that produce Otherworldy Combs
- Automatically turn in 2,500 Otherworldy Combs.

You are required to:

- Automate Advanced Rocketry's Precision Assembler, Cutting Machine, and Crystallizer.

You are required to:

- Automate creation of Air Balloons.
- Automatically turn in 10,000 Air Balloons.
§oThe most important meal of the day serving it up Gary's way...§r

This basic wand hold 25 of each aspect. Be careful when draining nodes with this wand, as it can sometimes fully drain a node and not allow it to re-charge an aspect. This can be avoided with better wands; however, for now, you are stuck with this one.

This wand does not need to be filled... yet!

Thaumonomicon: Right-click on a bookshelf block with your new wand to turn it into this book. This book tracks your progress through Thaumcraft.

Lexicon Botania: All information about Botaina's mechanics.


§aPLEASE NOTE: Both these book are NOT accurate as the recipes for some items are changed. Check NEI for up-to-date recipes. Recipes in these books are the default.

Right-click a thaumcraft table with a wand to get the arcane worktable.

Right-click a minecraft cauldron to convert it into a crucible. Place the crucible in the world with a heat source under it (fire, lava, etc...) Fill the crucible with a bucket of water. If you set it up properly, after a short while, the water in the crucible will start to boil. Anything that gets throw into the crucible will be used in a crafting recipe. Pipes can autofill the cauldron.

Place 2x thaumcraft tables right next to each other and right-click with scribing tools to convert the 2 tables into a research station.

The Research Table is how you learn how to make most Thaumcraft blocks and items. You have to unlock Research Notes in the Thaumonomicon using aspect points you get by scanning blocks, items, and especially Nodes using the Thaumometer. You have to scan things in a certain order. Paper and scribing tools will be used up as you do the research minigame.

Re-fill scribing tools with ink sacs to continue using them once they are depleted.
Reinforced Jetpack is just an upgraded version of the jetpack. Holds more RF, fly faster, and hover better. It just used more energy.

The Petal Apothecary is used to craft all flowers. Fill it with a bucket water, drop some petals in, and a vanilla wheat seed. This will create the flower.

You can easily automate this machine with droppers and a infinite water machine (such as a buildcraft pump).

The Pure Daisy is used to create Livingwood and Livingrock out of wood logs and smooth stone. Just place 8 of those materials around the flower, and after a few moments, the materials will be converted.

You can easily automate this with a timer, block breakers and block placers. You are going to need a lot of these materials all throughout your magical journey.

The Mana Pool is used to store generated Mana, which many things from Botania use as energy. You can craft things with it by throwing the ingredient into it if the pool has enough mana stored.

Mana Spreaders are how you move Mana. Put it down, shift + right-click a wand of the forest in bind mode first on the mana spreader and then on the mana pool. Mana generating flowers bound to the mana spreader will input mana into it, and then the mana spreader outputs it into the Mana Pool, or whatever else it's pointed at.
The wand of the forest is a tool used to see any Botania machine's crafting process or Mana amount by right-clicking or shift+right-clicking on it.

The Witches Oven is how you get many witchery-type ingredients. Input clay jars, furnace fuel, and saplings to craft different materials. Different saplings give different ingredients, as shown by NEI.

The Witches Oven requires arcane worktable crafting and mana pool conversion to make. Check NEI and google search to see how those crafting mechanics work.

Ensure you have enough fire and earth aspects in your thaumcraft wand to craft the arcane blocks in the arcane worktable.

Nodes are concentrated magical energy sources. They are found randomly throughout the world. The aspects within an aura node can be tapped and stored in a wand for later use.

If some of the aspect is left in a node it will automatically recharge (Even if the chunk is unloaded) so that you can go back to the node in the future. If there are no longer any aspects within a node, the node may disappear or worse. Large nodes can slowly drain vis from other smaller nodes if they are close enough, adding vis capacity to the larger node and damaging the smaller node.

Right-click on a node with your wand to drain one of the 6 aspects from the node into your wand.


§cIf all of a particular aspect is drained from the node, the aspect can disappear from the node, but it is not guaranteed. With the starting basic iron-capped wand, do not drain all of one aspect from the node.§r

The Kettle is used to craft similar to Thaumcraft's Crucible. Set a fire underneath it, give it some water, and throw in the ingredients. You cannot get items back after they have been thrown in. 

If the Kettle starts emitting white swirls and making noises, the brew is ready to take out. Right-click with an empty bottle to bottle it.

The Witchery altar gains altar power by having more nature stuff around it. You can also place items on top such as a wither skull or a candelabra.

It is a 3x2x1 multiblock structure.

I highly recommend you watch a YouTube video or google search how to research in Thaumcraft 4.

Ensure you have scribing tools and at least one sheet of paper in your inventory, then open up your thaumononicon, click on the 3rd tab on the left-hand side that says "Alchemy", locate the blinking entry that says "Nitor" and click it to gain the research note that you can then use to research the item in the research table.

After you have successfully researched nitor, craft it in the thaumcraft crucible you made earlier by throwing the required items into the boiling water.

Niter is a great alternative to torches for lighting things up and is as hot as lava.

Everything is made of 6 primal aspects. Those aspects can be combined to form compound aspects, but in the end, there are only 6. Like the infused shards you found. You noticed that those shards start to vibrate when you bring them next to something that is made of the respective aspect. Maybe you can create a device to actually "scan" items, and reveal their compounds? This could be very useful later on.

Just like the niter you just researched, the alchemical furnace needs to be researched before it can be crafted. If you cannot see the recipe of the item in NEI, it needs to be researched.

Research the "Essentia Distillation" entry that is linked after the nitor entry in the thaumononicon to gain that research note. Then research it to learn how to craft the alchemical furnace.

After it is researched, use the arcane worktable to craft the items needed to make up the alchemical furnace. Then craft the furnace itself. Keep an eye on your wand, you may need to re-fill it if a required aspect gets too low.


Distillation is a way of breaking down pretty much every block in the game into essentia. Place the Arcane Alembics on top of the Alchemical Furnace (maximum of 5 Arcane Alembics). Fuel for the furnace include Alumentum, and and solid fuel. Place virtually any item into the top slot of the furnace. It will break down into aspects. Aspects will go into the arcane alembic. If you have your goggles of revealing on, you can see what aspects went into the arcane alembics.


§cMake sure you keep your furnace as empty as possible. If it fills up with essentia, it can cause a large TPS drop.

The Daybloom Flower passively generate mana during the daytime. The Nightshade Flower generates during the night.

Both flowers only have a limited life-span.


The Blacker Lotus, when thrown into a Mana Pool that already contains any amount of Mana, generates 8k Mana.

The Blood Altar is the most important part of Blood Magic. This will eventually be a giant multiblock. At the highest tier, tier 6, it takes up a 23x23x9 space. Plan accordingly.

The sacrificial orb, when right clicked near a blood altar, removes a heart from your health and gives some life essence to the altar. It's also a great way to quickly kill youself.


§eIn order to make the Blood Altar, you are going to need to take a trip to the North Pole to collect some Snowy Bees to create Crushed Ice. You are also going to need a decent amount of Silk from bees. It is recommended that you focus on Bees for a bit before moving forward into Blood Magic.§r

See the "Infusion" entry under the "Artifice" tab in your thaumonomicon for more information on the infusion altar.

To balance the altar, try and have as much symmetry around it as possible while building and placing the pedestals. Mixed Crystal Clusters and Mob Skulls also help if placed in a symmetrical pattern.

Right-click on the Runic Matrix with a wand with at least 25 vis of each primal aspect to create the structure.
Best Jetpack ever

The Distillery is yet another crafting mechanic from Witchery. It uses Altar Power to function, so it must be placed near an Altar with sufficient Altar Power.

Place Clay Jars in the bottom slot, and the 2 ingredients in the slots above. The results are put into the slots to the right.

You are required to:

- Automate creation of Supreme Pizzas.
- Automatically turn in 10,000,000 Supreme Pizzas.
Allows more room for stuff in storage drawers.

Drawers can be locked or unlocked with the drawer key. When a drawer is locked, it will maintain its current item association even if the last item is removed. This will prevent pipes and other transport systems from re-filling that drawer with other items.

The COFH personal key uses your friends list of ThermalExpansion mods to determine who can access to your storage drawers.

Now that you got youself some pure certus quartz, you are going to need to make an inscriber block and power it with RF power.

The 4 inscriber presses can be copied from other players in the server or created yourself using a TON of power (50 million RF) and a brand-new fully-activated division sigil (drops from the wither).

I highly recommend you try and trade with another player or shop because they are very easy to copy but very hard to craft.

Use the inscriber and the respective material to create all three of the processors which are used in basically all AE2 crafting recipes. I highly recommend you automate everything in AE2 up to this point to make your life much easier down the road.
Just like items, fluids can also be compressed and stored in a ME Network. It only requires a few blocks to be attached to an existing ME Network to function.

The ME Controller allows for more than 8 channels to be added to a ME Network. The ME Controller takes power and allows for either 8 or 32 channels on each side of the block.

Multiblock Controllers can be build in a fairly free form, however there are a few rules that must be followed:

1: All ME Controller blocks on a ME Network must be connected; else the blocks will turn red.
2: The size of the ME Controller must be within 7x7x7; else it will turn red.
3: A ME Controller can have 2 adjacent blocks in at most 1 axis; if a block violates this rule, it will disable and turn white.

ME Dense Cables can carry 32 channels and you can see a visual representation of them; however, you cannot connect any busses to them. You must branch off of these Dense Cables with smart cables first.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Converting RF Power to AE2 Power
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Many machine in the Applied Energistics mod require AE2 power instead of RF power. The Energy Acceptor converts RF power into AE power.

Energy cells store converted power in the ME network for later use. They do not accept power directly but are used to add additional power storage to a ME network.

Note: 1 RF = 1 AE
Upgraded version of the normal machine frame used to build more complicated blocks

The BC Quarry uses RF to mine an area down to Bedrock. By default, it has an area of 9x9x4, which can be changed using Land Marks. Once it has RF, it starts to clear the area required and build the frame. Once that happens, it starts mining and putting the blocks into the inventory or pipe above it.

The Quarry is not upgradable. A redstone signal will turn it off. The more RF you give it, the faster it goes. The Quarry gets a bit confused with Lava, so try and pump out the lava before of after the quarry operation then run it again.

The Quarry Fixer, when placed beside a Quarry and Right-Clicked, removes all liquids from the Quarry dig area and places stone in the walls. This helps prevent lag from liquids constantly updating in the quarried area.

The Ender Quarry is an advanced version of a regular quarry. When a border is defined, either by a square of fences or 3 Ender-Markers, RF power is supplied, and an inventory (or a pipe) is attached to the block, it will start replacing every block from a few blocks above the square defined all the way down to bedrock with dirt.

Ender-Markers are the alternative to a square of fences to define the area an Ender Quarry will mine. Place the first one next to the Ender Quarry, and run in any cardinal direction. Make sure you run in a straight line. Once you've forgotten how far away the quarry is, place down the Ender-Marker. If it is on either the same x or z coordinate, particles will come out of the Ender-Marker towards the main one. Go back to the quarry and do the same thing, but in a perpindicular direction. Distance between Ender-Markers does nothing except give you more materials. As far as I know, there is no limit to how far away it can be. Although, do make sure nobody's base is in the middle, that would be rude. Once the 3 are placed correctly, right click on the Ender Quarry and it will try to define an area. If it works, congrats. If it doesn't, one of the Ender-Markers isn't in the right place.

Blocks mined are not destroyed, but replaced with Dirt. This is great for preventing lag, as no lighting or fluid updates are made whatsoever. If there is no inventory to push into, or if that inventory is full, the quarry will temporarily stop until there is room to push items into. For this reason, it is best to automate pulling items out of the quarry. Ender Chests are great for this, as you can have one Ender Chest at your Quarry, and the other at your ore processing. Be careful what upgrades you put on the Ender Quarry, they can increase the RF cost by an extremely high amount.

Tesseracts are used to teleport items, liquid, and energy within/across dimensions simultaneously. It interacts with most mods' transport and energy systems, such as Itemduct, Pipe, Fluiduct, Fluid Pipe. The Tesseract is protected, so only the Owner can remove it. The chunks containing the Tesseracts must be loaded into memory for the network to function. It can be picked up and moved by Shift+Right-clicking with a Wrench or Crescent Hammer and the configuration settings will be preserved.
These high-tiered metals are used to make some of the best items and blocks in this modpack.

Wood and Emerald pipes are for extracting items from any container. Emerald is faster and has a filter available.

Cobblestone, Stone, and Quartz pipes are basic pipes that carry items along the pipe network. The three types will only connect to the same type of pipe not to each other. Cobblestone is slowest, quartz is fastest.

Gold pipes boost the speed of items passing through them.

Iron pipes have only one output. It can be changed with a wrench.

Sandstone pipes only connect to pipes not to machines or other inventories.

Obsidian pipes will pick up items off the ground. Their collection range will increase when powered by an engine.

Clay pipes connect to an inventory and will try and push any items flowing through the pipe into that inventory.

Stripe pipe will place, pick up or use an object that is in front of it when powered by an engine.

Diamond pipes are able to sort items that pass through it. They have up to 6 colored outputs that will hold up to 9 different items for each output side.

The Lazuli and Daizuli pipes work together to sort items based on an assigned color-code.
Lazuli pipes paint anything that passes through it to a configured color set by right-clicking with a wrench on the pipe.
Daizuli pipes sort already painted items and send them out of different sides of the pipe for color-based routing.

The Mattock is a versatile farming tool. Its primary purpose is to till soil; however, it also works somewhat like an axe and a shovel, but is not a replacement for either.

It can break all wood-based blocks and dirt as fast as their respective tool can (out of the same material); however, it does not mine other "soil" blocks such as sand, gravel, or soul sand any faster than your hand.

Right-clicking grass or dirt blocks near water source blocks will hoe the ground on the ground. Right-clicking grass blocks away from water source blocks will turn the block to dirt with around a 5% chance of dropping a random crop seed.

- All parts of the mattock must be made out of copper (Hold Control while hovering over the mattock to see the parts needed).
- The mattock must be fully repaired.
- The mattock must be named "Pablo".
- The mattock must be brand new and never used before.
The Floater allows the airship to float on water and not sink too deep. This is also a good base for your airship.

Repeatable - 5 Days
$500 to buy a Basic Chunkloader that keeps a 3x3 area (9 chunks) loaded when you are logged onto the server.

The Chunkloader requires a $1 Bill for every 12 hours of operation. A full stack of $1 Bills will keep the chunkloader working for a little over a month (32 days). Pipes and machine are NOT able to interact with the chunkloaders, they must be filled manually by a player.


§cView the "Advanced Chunkloader" incentive to learn how to upgrade the Chunkloader to be active even when you are not logged into the server.
Storage upgrades allow more space for the items in the drawers. Shift+right-click with an empty hand to view the upgrade slots in the barrel.

The Air Balloon is used to give ships the ability to fly if at least 40% of the ship is made using Air Balloons. That ship could ascend and descend using the UP Arrow and DOWN Arrow respectively (by default).

The void upgrade will delete any excess items that enter the storage drawer after the drawer is 100% full.

The status upgrade will display a bar to show total remaining space left for items.
A Deep Storage Unit can hold up to 2,000,000,000 of one type of item and preserves the items stored when the block is picked up.
No Description

The Trash Can has one slot that immediately voids the items placed in. The single slot can also accept a configured Item Filter so that the Trash Can will only accept the items configured in the filter from pipes.

Can hold 127 Stacks of a single item. or 65 Stacks of 63 different items.

Inserted into an ME Drive, ME Chest or ME IO Port, data can be stored on the Cell from the ME Network. Storage Cells can be formatted using an ME Performatter. Shift+Right-click in hand to separate its Storage Component from the Advanced Storage Housing.
Can store 8,128 buckets of any liquid and up to 5 different liquid types.

The Drawer Controller allows you to access every single connected Storage Drawer from sources like the Inventory Panel, ME Storage Bus, or just right clicking the controller with a hand to fill connected drawers.

The Drawer Controller doesn't have to be directly touching every Drawer, it just has to be touching one that is touching another that is touching another etc. So if you have a wall of Drawers, so long as the Controller is touching one of them, you can access them all from it.
Can store 1,024 Essentia and up to 12 different Essentia types.
Blackout Curtains reduces light that passes through them by approximately half, while still allowing entities to pass through. This is useful for doors that need to keep the light out at all times.
