betterquesting:10.name:8: Sticks and Stones Broke My Bones
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You are required to:

- Turn in 1 billion cobblestone...
- Yes! 1,000,000,000 blocks of cobblestone!

Refinery uses RF power to:

1x Oil -> 1x Fuel
4x Biomass -> 1x Ethanol

Fuel and Ethanol are both MUCH better power sources than oil and biomass.

Normal: Restores 18 health over time, every 50 ticks.
Extended: Restores 36 health over time, every 50 ticks.
Potent: Restores 18 health over time, every 25 ticks.

The Silk Touch Upgrade gives the Ender Quarry the Silk Touch effect and increases the power used by the quarry 1.5 times.

The Fortune I Upgrade gives the Ender Quarry a Fortune I effect.

The Pump Upgrade allows the quarry to pump liquids blocks as water and lava. The quarry need a tank and a chest for the items.

The Speed I Upgrade multiplies both the speed and power cost of the quarry.

The World Hole Upgrade will, instead of replacing mined blocks with dirt, will leave them empty. This upgrade will cause more lag.

Normal: Increased speed by 20% for 3 minutes.
Extended: Increased speed by 20% for 8 minutes.
Potent: Increased speed by 40% for 1.5 minutes.

The Combustion Engine is the most powerful engine in BuildCraft, and it provides 10-60 Redstone Flux per tick (RF/t) depending on the fuel source.

Use the rewards you get in this quest to start bulding an airship to collect oil on the go.... Or, you know, don't.

Dynamos generates RF at 80 RF/t. Dynamos will only output power in one direction, the other sides of the block can be used to connect ducting.

The Steam Dynamo requires Steam to generate power; Steam may be supplied directly via pipes, or be supplied with Water and a solid fuel such as Coal.

The Compression Dynamo is fueled by fluid fuel (such as oil, fuel, or ethanol) and coolant (such as water).

The Reactant Dynamo is designed to use the alchemy reaction of a solid catalyst with a liquid fuel to enhance the energy production.
I want some fuel to fill my stomach please...

Normal: Gives immunity to damage from all heat-related damage for 3 minutes
Extended: Gives immunity to damage from all heat-related damage for 8 minutes

Nearly every machine and power generation block in this pack requires chipsets which need microchips. Microchips are purposly made to be annoying to craft to get you to automate them as early as possible.

§aTrust me, you will want to automate this!

Although many of the questing tasks can be submitted directly through your inventory (including liquids) sometimes you need a more automated solution. This is where the Object Submission Station (OSS) comes in handy.

Tasks supporting the OSS can be selected through the built in interface to enable its use. Once setup, liquids and items can be either piped in or dropped into the interface's input slot. The machine will not void items or liquids if no task is selected or if it has already been completed making it relatively safe from accidental item/fluid deletion. Multiple OSS are also capable of taking on separate sub-tasks under the same quest simultaneously.

Link this quest to the OSS using its GUI. Once you have the infrastructure available, hook up an infinite water supply to the OSS to start pumping water to complete this quest automatically.

Or you could just turn in 1024 buckets of water manually if you are... like... dumb.

You are required to:

- Travel to all 4 corners of the playable overworld. From ice-cold oceans North to bone-dry deserts South.


§oMake sure to cycle through the 4x quests with the arrows at the bottom-right corner of this screen.§r

Thermal Expansion Machines can have augments installed to improve certain properties or to change how it works. The amount of augments that can be installed depends on the machine's tier.


Integrated Modular Framework: allows a Player to configure the sides of a machine as input or output. Without it, machines use the previously defined or default configuration. The color setting of a side determines whether it acts as input, output or neither. Depending on the machine, a side may have up to seven choices of color:
- Disabled (blank): This disables the side from any interaction with other blocks or conduits.
§9- Input:§r items are inserted on this side (combined input on multiple output machines).
§a- Output:§r machines will output contents of all output slots out of this side.
§c- Primary output: §rmultiple output machines will output contents of their first output slot out of this side.
§e- Secondary output:§r multiple output machines will output contents of their second output slot out of this side.
§2- Primary input:§r multiple input machines will input items from this side into its first input slot.
§5- Secondary input:§r multiple input machines will input items from this side into its secondary input slot.§r

Integrated Servo Mechanism: gives machines the ability to automatically eject their output to a connected inventory or transport system, such as an Itemduct. Without it, machines must have their output emptied by hand or extracted by a Servo or Wooden Transport Pipe.

Integrated Redstone Circuit: allows a Player to control how a Redstone signal will affect the machine. It is integrated in all machines. Without it, machines use the default setting.
- Ignored (default): The machine will constantly operate regardless of Redstone signal.
- Low: The machine will NOT operate if there is a Redstone signal.
- High: The machine will only operate when receiving a Redstone signal.

Wrenches can rotate and configure many machines and blocks by right-clicking on the block you want rotated.

The Multimeter allows you to measure power in various ways. It can read network saturation, conduit averages, and the energy requested by a machine.

A flux capacitor is an item that stores Redstone Flux and can use it to charge items in a player’s inventory.

A charged flux capacitor can be activated and deactivated by using it while sneaking. When active, a flux capacitor charges certain items that can hold Redstone Flux in a player’s inventory.
Holds more power...

The charger is used to create charged certus quartz from normal certus quartz. It can also be used to charge various tools from this mod.

RF power must be either supplied to the bottom/top or a wood crank attached to the top (like the grindstone) if you want to take that route.

Here is $10k cash for all your troubles dealing with me so far. <3

It's My Money and I Want It Now!

Using the Builder it is possible to copy, move, or swap areas in the world to other locations. It needs energy to do that and in case of the 'copy' mode it also needs an inventory on top or below it containing the blocks to build with.

The Builder Block can also quarry a selected area (using a quarry shape card) and will place the items collected in a nearby inventory.

A Strongbox acts like a chest however, it will retain its contents when the block is broken. It provides a total of 18 slots to store items in. Aside from being able to store items, the Strongbox offers security features. It can be set to public access, owner only access or restricted access. The latter allows anyone who's on the player's COFH friends list to access the inventory. Also, items can only be pumped into and out of strongboxes when they are set to public access. Itemducts seem to be the only transport system that connects to them as well.

Strongboxes cannot be broken with a pickaxe. To remove it, the player must Shift+Right-click the Strongbox with a wrench.
-
Caches are enabled just in case a cetain mod doesn't interact with the storage drawers mod propertly.

Frames can connect together and "stick" to adjacent blocks. When a frame is pushed/pulled, the entire structure it is connected with is pushed (provided there is room). You can right-click a side with a wrench to 'close' it and prevent frames from sticking to block or frame on that side.

A Frame pusher/puller cannot move itself but it can move other Pusher/Pullers.

It charges Redstone Flux-powered items held or worn by entities that touch it, as well as dropped items that touch it.

The Plate can be placed on any side of a block.

Dynamos can have augments installed to improve certain properties or to change how it works. The amount of augments that can be installed depends on the dynamo’s tier.


Secondary Gearbox: saves 10% energy cost while burning fuel.

Secondary Transmission Coil: uses 2x the amount of fuel for 2x the amount of power.

Excitation Field Limiter: sets the minimum output on dynamo to 0 RF/t. This is useful as the dynamo will not waste any fuel once it is full of RF.

Worn in the helmet slot, these goggles allow their wearer to see a number of magical phenomena:
- Nodes are visible at a great distance, regardless of obstructions.
- At closer range, the aspects and strength of a node is displayed.
- The amount and aspect of essentia contained in jars, alembics, crucibles, and similar containers are similarly displayed.
- The progress of an Infusion can be monitored, with the essentia "owed" visible above the runic matrix.

Every point of vis is critical, so make yourself some magical robes to help conserve how much you use. Later you can make even better robes. They don't offer much in protection, so remember to change before going out into the wild.

The Ring of Correction, when equipped in a Baubles ring slot, will switch the tool in the player's hand with the correct tool from their inventory if the one they are using is not used to mine the block effectively. It only works on Mana-using pickaxes, shovels and axes.

The Ring of Magnetization, when equipped in a Baubles ring slot, will pull dropped items to you within a small ranges. Sneaking disables the effect. The ring will try and pull items that are behind cover so watch out for that if you have a build that uses, for example, droppers to automate something.
No Description
No Description
The Multiblock Turbine is a subline feature of Big Reactors. It is a large, complex multi-block structure built from Turbine parts that consumes steam to produce RF and water.

Hand in 100 buckets of gelid cryotheum.
This liquid is one of the best fluids to use in the reactor to cool it down.
The Cyanite Reprocessor machine processes 2 ingots of nuclear waste into 1 ingot of fresh, reactor-ready fuel. It requires 1 bucket (1000mB) of water for each cycle.

The Fermenter can turn a wide variety of plant material into Biomass liquid, as well as the creation of Short Mead with Honeydew drops.

To operate, the Fermenter needs a constant supply of RF, water, any plant matter in the top slot, and a fertilizer (Fertilizer, Mulch, or Compost) in the bottom slot.

Once in operation, the Fermenter will break down the plant into Biomass, the amount of Biomass is determined by how much Sappiness the sapling has. You can further increase the output by replacing the water with liquid honey or fruit juice.

To create Short Mead, you will need to supply the Fermenter with liquid honey, not water or fruit juice. Honeydew will go in the top slot, and the fertilizer item will go in the bottom slot as normal. Two Honeydew drops and one capsule worth of liquid honey will produce one capsule worth of Short Mead.


Biomass can be refined with a Buildcraft Refinery into Ethanol which can be burned in any engine that accepts normal liquid fuel.

The Pipette is used to take liquids out of Forestry machines. It can hold up one bucket of liquid.
I want some ethanol to fill my stomach please...

A bed allows a player to sleep and to reset their spawn point to within a few blocks of the bed.

The Sleeping Bag can be used to sleep without using a bed and without changing the respawn point for the player. The bag is activated by wearing it in the chestplate slot at night or by activating it and right-clicking.

The Tape Measure is used to measure distances. It has 2 modes, a per coordinate measurement which returns the x, y, and z measurements between points and absolute measurement mode which gives a straight distance in meters (blocks) between 2 points.

The tape measure will also place down a marker pole block on the block you click on (if it can) and display the distance from the marker pole to the player in real time right below the player’s crosshair.

The Laser Drill consumes large amounts of RF to artificially gather ore from the void.

The Laser Drill does not directly accept energy; instead, it is powered by up to four nearby Laser Drill Pre-chargers surrounding the Laser Drill. Once the Laser drill has an un-obstruted view of either bedrock or the void, it will start attempting to artificially create ores from under the world.

The Chronotyper will examine a 5x5 area in front of it, for either baby or adult animals (configurable in the machine), and move them to the back side of the machine.

The Breeder will breed all animals in a 5x5 area in front of it. The Breeder will feed an animal whatever normally is required for breeding (wheat for cows, carrots for pigs, etc). The Breeder will only feed the animals if they are an adult or if it can accept it.

The Mob Counter will output a redstone signal when a mob is detected in the 5x5x5 cube area in front of it. For every additional mob in the detection area, the strength of the redstone signal increases by one until the maximum strength of the signal is reached. All mobs, friendly and aggressive are detected, as well as players.

The Mob Router is used to move mobs from one side of it to the other. It has an interface that can specify what type of mob such as villagers/skeltons and go as far as to only pick villagers that look the same or take the skeletons out of your wither skeleton farm. When moving the mobs it outputs them in a 1x1 square on the other side so you could possibly use this to consolidate wither skeletons into a 1x1 space to behead them or even use the technology to make a mob grinder for XP and rare drops such as heart canisters.

The Auto-Enchanter, when supplied with Essence and power, will enchant items. When enchanting a book with the Auto-Enchanter multiple enchantments may be placed on the book, of any type; this includes enchantments not normally obtainable, such as Soul Stealer, as well as enchantments for different item types.

The Auto-Disenchanter will extract a randomly chosen enchantment from an enchanted item and store it in a Book, turning it into an Enchanted Book. To operate, it requires you to insert an enchanted item and a regular minecraft book, along with a supply of power. When an item has been disenchanted, it will take some damage, which can break the item if it was already sufficiently damaged.

The Auto-Anvil automates tool repair. The Auto-Anvil consumes more mob essence and power for each level of Experience required. Auto-Anvil cannot be used to rename items or blocks.

The Auto-Spawner uses RF and Mob Essence to spawn the mob inside of the Safari Net. 

The Exact Copy mode uses more RF and Mob Essence, but spawns an exact copy of the mob you caught. This means if you caught something with low health, the mobs spawned will have low health. If you caught a Wither Skeleton, Wither Skeletons will be spawned in the Overworld.

Shift+right-click the Safari Net Launcher to set it to Catch Mode. If you have a Safari Net in your inventory and you shoot it at a mob, it will be put into the Safari Net.

The MFR Grinder instantly kills regular mobs like Creepers, Skeletons, Zombies, and Wither Skeletons. It uses RF to run, and each mob kill produces a small amount of liquid Mob Essence. Mob drops are ejected out the back of the machine. The Grinder has a range of 5x5x3, which can NOT be upgraded.

The Slaughterhouse is like the MFR Grinder; however, mobs killed by the machine do not drop anything. The Slaughterhouse gets some Meat, and rarely Pink Slime.

The Rancher is used to farm items that can be obtained from mobs without killing them, such as Wool from Sheep or milk from cows.

The Planter, when placed centered and below a 3x3 set of blocks will plant seeds and saplings in its inventory to the soil above when supplied with power. It is necessary to use the appropriate soil for the kind of seed or sapling you are using (e.g. Netherwarts requires soul sand).

If used in conjunction with a Fertilizer the growth of the plant/tree is greatly increased.

The planter will try to lay out crops according to the layout of its 3x3 inventory, with the top middle slot being north. This becomes more viable and useful with range upgrades. Range upgrades are in addition to the starting size. For example, a +1 range upgrade will plant in a 5x5 area.

The Harvester will harvest crops in front of it in a 3x3 square. It will output the collected items in a chest, pipe or other item container, on the connected side. The Harvester also produces sludge for each operation which can be piped out. Held Sludge slows the harvest speed. When the sludge tank is full, the Harvester ceases to function.

Moreover, the Harvester has additional configuration options in its GUI to allow the harvesting of blocks of leaves, harvesting of small mushrooms, and harvesting jungle wood (option for Cocoa Beans).

Wood and Emerald Kinesis Pipe  (320, 2560 RF/t)
Allows Engines to output directly into the pipe.

Cobblestone, Stone, Quartz Kinesis Pipe (80, 160, 320 RF/t)
Used to separate Cobblestone, Stone, & Quartz Pipes.

Sandstone Kinesis Pipe (320 RF/t)
Only connects to other pipes not machines.

Iron Kinesis Pipe (1280 RF/t)
Can be configured to limit amount of energy.

Golden, Diamond Kinesis Pipe (2560, 10,240 RF/t)
Dense power pipe.


Note: If more power is trying to go through a pipe than it can handle, a bottleneck will form and the inside the pipe will become red to indicate that.

Fluxducts are an upgrade to Buildcraft's kinesis pipes.

Leadstone Fluxduct
200, RF/t

Hardened  Fluxduct
800, RF/t

Redstone Fluxduct 
8,000 RF/t

Resonant Fluxduct
32,000 RF/t

The Crystal Growth Accelerator is used to accelerate the process of purifying crystals, which allows you to create Pure Certus Quartz Crystal, Pure Nether Quartz Crystal and Pure Fluix Crystal.

This machine must be powered by a ME network (not RF) via the top or bottom of the block. Unlike most machine, this block will always draw power even if it is not doing anything. I highly recommend you find a way to cut power to the machine while it is not in use.

Crystal Seeds must be in an adjacent water block to be effected, the seeds will shimmer more rapidly when in the presence of a powered Crystal Growth Accelerator.

The more of these Accelerators are around the pool of water, the faster the seed will grow.

ME glass cables are the simplest cable available. each cable can transfer ME power and up to 8 network channels. It comes in 17 diffrent colors.

ME smart cables can also only hold 8 channels at once, but you see a visual representation of the amount of channels being used up.

A bus which functions similarly to ME glass cables or other cables, but it allows its connection state to be toggled via a redstone signal. This allows you to cut off a section of a ME network.

The ME Drive holds 10 storage cells so you can tightly pack your storage into a very small space. The block show their contents and the storage cell status on the front of the drive face.

Red - Indicates the Storage Cell is Full.
Orange - Indicates the Storage Cell cannot hold any more types, but it can store more items.
Green - Indicates the cell can hold more types, or more items.
Black - Indicates there is no channel, or power is offline.

The ME Terminal gives you access to a ME Network's Networked Storage. It has the ability to sort and search, as well as filter by using View Cell. It requires a Channel to function

Its important to note, that without a ME Network this block does nothing. Its only useful when combined with a way to input, and output items, and requires a constant supply of AE2 power to function. More power for each storage cell in the rack. The ME Interface allows you to view, input, and output items to/from the ME Network it is attached to.

The ME Storage Bus, when attached to another inventory block in the world lets you access that inventory via networked functions. This allows you to use chests, barrels, or other types of item storage in your networks.

The ME Drive, ME Storage Bus, and ME Interface require one channel each to function. Only 8 channels are supported on each basic ME network. If you exceed the 8-channel limit, the entire system with stop working. If you require more than 8 channels, ME Controllers must be connected to the network.

AE2's probably best feature is Autocrafting. This allows you to automatically craft whatever you define, which saves a surprising amount of time.

The Crafting CPU is a multiblock. It must be a cuboid, meaning it has 6 sides maximum. It is made up of Crafting Co-Processing Units and Crafting Storages. The more Crafting CPUs, the faster it can craft (so long as they don't require outside machines, which can only be sped up with their own mechanics). The more Crafting Storage you have, the more complicated of a recipe you can make. Having multiple Multiblocks allows you to autocraft multiple things at once.

The ME Pattern Terminal allows you to set recipes that can be autocrafted, either through regular crafting or through machines. You need Blank Patterns to begin with. For crafting table recipes, input the recipe to the crafting table GUI to the left and hit the Encode Pattern Button and pull out the Encoded Pattern. For processing patterns, for instance Alloy Smelter or other things like that, click the Crafting Table to the right to switch modes. Then, put the inputs to the left and outputs to the right. Keep clicking to put more of the same item in if you need multiple or receive multiple of one of the items.

The ME Interface is where you connect your ME System to processing or crafting. For processing, put the ME Interface (preferably the panel version, as you can put multiple in one block, and you specify which side of the cable) next to a machine, like an Alloy Smelter. Then, put a processing recipe into the bottom slots of the ME Interface. Connect an Import Bus to the machine to pull the finished item back into the ME System. Bingo presto, automatic processing. For regular crafting, see the next task. ME Interfaces take up a channel each.

The ME Import Bus pulls items from the inventory it is pointed at and places them into the ME Network if space is available. You can specify which items it will pull out via the UI, else it tries to pull out any item in the adjacent inventory. 

The ME Export Bus extracts items from the ME Network and places them into the inventory it faces. You must configure which items it will insert, leaving the configuration blank will result in nothing. The Export Bus will try to export any of the items on its list skipping over those it cannot fit into the destination.

The ME Import and Export Bus each require one channel to function.
A Drum can store 256 buckets of liquid. When broken with a pickaxe, the drum will be dismantled and keeps the stored liquid. Liquids may be pumped in or out from any side of the Drum.

A Bedrockium Drum is an upgraded version of the regular drum and can store up to 65,536 buckets of liquid. When broken with a pickaxe, the drum will be dismantled and keeps the stored liquid. Liquids may be pumped in or out from any side of the Drum.

OpenBlocks's tanks each can hold 16 buckets of liquid, and multiple tanks will link together in any direction, unlike most multiblock tank designs which must be built in certain dimensions.

The XP Drain drains your XP from you inventory when you stand on it and stores it in a tank if there is one under it.

The XP Shower will to pour out the experience in the form of experience orbs if connected to a tank with liquid xp in it. When a redstone signal is applied, the shower will deactivate.

Liquid XP is a great way of storing your player's experience to save it for a later date. Remember, dying removes all your xp from your player.

Glowstone Glass emits light around the edges. Eliminating the need for an external light source.

Obisidan Glass is blast resistant just like normal obsidian.

Dark Glass is translucent to look through but does not allow Light to pass through it. This makes it ideal for building mob spawning rooms and other structures where being able to see in without interfering with the lighting is desired.

To hatch a dragon egg, place the egg block then right-click it. The egg will start to hatch, which will take a while.

-Once grown up, you can tame the dragon with raw fish. It will then follow and protect you like other pets.
-You can command tamed dragons to lay down or stand up with the bone item.
-To ride a tamed dragon, use a saddle on it, then right click it without holding an action item.
-To heal injured dragons, feed it with raw fish, chicken, beef or porkchop (four hearts) or with rotten flesh (two hearts).
-You can control the dragon with the Carrot On A Stick while riding it.

The origin of the hostility is unknown, but light is vital in the Deep Dark; spending too long in the darkness will leave the Player as prey for the Shadows, which attack in half-heart ticks. Invisible, the Shadows can prove deadly if the Player is carelessly exploring, or run off into the dark to avoid attack. Fortunately, light keeps the Shadows at bay.

Mobs spawned in this dimension possess double their normal health.


§cPlease don't tell America about the Drum §mfilled with oil§r§c §cyou get as a reward!

Also known as The End of Time, this is a void dimension where there is nothing anywhere except a single platform with a streetlamp and The Last Villager. This dimension is a very noticeable reference to Chrono Trigger, but it is also a great place to just build for people who like to build in void dimensions.

Feed Station will periodically feed a nearby animal with respective food. The frequency is random and every feed item will feed two animals. Additionally, the Feed Station will only feed animals ready to mate. As a bonus, Pigs, Chickens, Wolves and Cats will even birth entire litters of offspring, greatly boosting your farm output.

Packing animals too tight will not allow animals to breed, and in fact may even start despawning if they are packed tightly enough. Providing a Redstone current to the Feed Station will disable it. The Feed Station can cover a 5x5 area.

The Sound Muffler will reduce the volume of most sounds in an 7 block radius by 90 percent. This can, for example, be used to quiet down farms with many animals.

The Rain Muffler will silence any rain sounds in a radius of 64 blocks. The Rain Muffler will not activate instantly, as it takes a few seconds for already playing rain sounds to finish.

The player can also right-click the block while empty-handed to silence rain for themselves, regardless of the block being present nearby. Right-clicking the block undoes this, letting the player hear rain again.

A Witches Cauldron is made by placing a regular Cauldron in the world, and then using Anointing Paste on it.

To brew a potion, cast a ritual or create an item, the cauldron must first be filled with water (3 buckets total). Place a heat source under the block and wait for the water to boil. Once the water boils, add ingredients into the cauldron for the desired item.
Steve's Workshop adds a modular Production Table that can make crafting and cooking items much easier.

The Safari Net is an item that allows the Player to capture mobs. It will not capture a mob boss. This safari net can only be used once on a single mob then it is deleted. 

The safari net launcher can capture and release mobs from a distance. The release and capture mode is set on the Launcher with Shift+Right-click. The Safari Net will change colour depending on the mob inside.

Water is not infinite in this pack. A water tank (build the same way as a coke oven) constantly collects water from the environment around it. The refill rate is determined by the biome it's in.

If rain touches the tower, it generates faster. It can hold up to 400 buckets of water.

With this upgrade on the Atlas, when you die, you will spawn with an Eternal Compass that will lead you back to your point of death. It functions just like a waypoint compass.

Max Level: 1
Works on: Atlas (BiblioCraft)
Easily the best armor in the game - hands down - no contest.
MFR Fertile Farmland does not require a water source block nearby to keep the crop hydrated.

How do you turn a Minecraft house into a home? A warm hearth, a carpeted floor and some pictures on the walls all help. But for me, the crowning glory of a well-appointed residence is a jukebox.	


§aChoose your armor reward piece carefully! Tailored to your needs.

A tripwire is used to detect entities (players, mobs, items, etc.) that come in contact with the string in between the two hooks.

In order to function correctly, a tripwire hook must be part of a "tripwire circuit": a straight line of string (1-40 blocks) with a tripwire hook attached to both sides of it. It will emit a redstone signal out of both hooks if the string is stepped on or cut (except by shears).

Connect the tripwire to TNT and watch your friend walk over it.

Flood Gate is used to place liquid blocks in the world, making it a reverse version of a Pump. However, unlike the Pump, the Flood Gate doesn't require power to operate.

Giving enough time, Flood Gates can be used for creating artificial lakes or even entire oceans.

BuildCraft Pump is used to collect cool liquids, such as oil and water. This pump cannot pump very hot or very cold luqids such as lava.

A pump can draw from a 64 block radius and straight down until it hits a solid block.


§eNote: This pump does NOT need RF power to operate. A few redstone engines can power it just fine.

The Ender-Thermic Pump is a low-lag liquid pump designed specifically for lava in the Nether.

When it pumps up a lava source block, it instantly replaces it with a Stone block and doesn't cause a block-update. It also acts as a chunk-loader, keeping itself and the bare minimum of chunks loaded in order to pump lava. This Pump is able to pump lava through solid blocks below it.

When holding any wand or staff (scepters cannot use foci), the player can press and hold the G key (default) for a pop-up display of all foci in their inventory, and use the cursor to choose among them. Pressing Shift+G will remove the current focus from their wand without placing another one.

§9Fire§r
Shoots flame and sets mobs afire. It does not set blocks afire; however, the Alchemist's Fire upgrade can allow it to do so.

§9Shock§r
"Target-seeking" electricity attack with considerable damage.

§9Frost§r
Shoots balls of ice, which do considerable damage but are prone to bouncing around.

§9Equal Trade§r
Needs to be primed with a result block before use, by shift+right-clicking on a target block will trade that block for the result block, taken from your inventory (right-click to do a bunch of similar blocks at once). You must have a supply of the correct block in your inventory. Blocks which don't drop themselves (such as smooth stone or grass) will be returned as their drops. Un-minable blocks such as glass will be destroyed. Note that possible upgrades include Treasure (equivalent to the Fortune enchantment), or Silk Touch.

§9Crafting§r
Used to open 3x3 crafting grid anywhere. It can be enchanted with Storage, Gratis and Transposing. It also allows the player to perform recipes in Arcane Worktable, using the Vis from the wand.


Given that a player will develop a considerable number of foci, they are advised to carry a Focus Pouch with them to contain all the foci in a single inventory slot.

Everfull will constantly refill itself with water for free.

Everburn will use ignis vis to refill itself with lava.

This wand holds 50 of each aspect instead of 25. It is also will not kill off aspects in nodes as long as you have the advance node tapping research completed.

Charge up the wand all the way using nodes throughout the world.

This wand holds 100 of each aspect.

§aIn order to craft this wand, you need to be wearing armor that will discount the Vis amount to around 90%.§r

You want another Node? Turn in 16 of each primal shard.

Balanced Shards need to be crafted.
The Tool Forge replaces your Tool Station. It allows you to make more advanced tools like the Hammer or the Scythe.

The Compacting Drawer stores a block in 3 forms. For instance, if you put a Gold Ingot in it, you can pull out ingots, nuggets, or blocks, depending on how much you have. You can also use it to store Cobblestone, and it keeps it as regular Cobblestone, Compressed Cobblestone, and Double Compressed Cobblestone.

The Compacting Drawer's maximum storage is based on the highest denomination. That is, it can hold 16 stacks of Iron Blocks, for instance.
-

Steve's Factory Manager allows for extremely precise and complex automation that pipes can't do. You can pull and push from specific slots of an inventory, interact with Redstone, change Signs, break and place blocks, and so much more.

Machine Inventory Manager: Main machine that is required in any setup. Manages all blocks along the network.

Inventory Cable: Used for to connect blocks to the network.

Inventory Relay: Interacts with inventories of adjacent entities (such as a moving minecart chest), but not players.

Advanced Inventory Relay: As the Inventory Relay, except that it can interact with players.

Redstone Emitter: Can add/subtract/change redstone signal on any side of the block.

Redstone Receiver: Reads redstone signal on any side of the block.

Item Valve: Picks up item entities from the world. Items falling in pickup range obey the standard delay that a player has when dropping items. Can pickup from a 7x7x7 area in front or a 3 block radius around it.

Rapid Item Valve: As the Item Valve, but does not have the standard delay on picking up items.

Block Detector: Detects when block updates occur (such as blocks being placed or crop growing to the next state).

Block Gate: Can break and pickup blocks (input mode). Or can place blocks in the world or drop items on the ground (output mode). In output mode items are always placed 2 blocks away if possible, then 1 block away if possible, then dropped on the ground. Can use an item if it has a use action (like a hoe), but it will also drop the item after use. Items can be pumped into the item and they will be immediately placed.

Sign Updater: Can update vanilla signs.

Cable Camouflage: Can alter any block face to mimic another block.

Double-Sided Cable Camouflage: As the Cable Camouflage except that you also have access to the inside faces of the block (only seen when using transparent faces, like glass). These can also be conditionally set based on viewing side of the block (a real life example would be a one-way mirror).

Transforming Cable Camouflage: As the Double-Sided Cable Camouflage, except that you can also alter the block's 3D dimension in the world (similar to a ForgeMultipart block), and it's collision detection.

Cable Cluster: Condenses other Steve's Factory Manager blocks into a single block (except for the Machine Inventory Manager and Inventory Cable), and is capable of performing any of the tasks those containing blocks can do.

Advanced Cable Cluster: As the Cable Cluster except that it also acts as an Inventory Cable.

The Elven knowledge points to a ritual to summon the Gaia Guardian. The Gaia Guardian will drop materials and tools that will allow you to create the most powerful items Botania has to offer, but the fight is no joke. 

The Ritual to summon the Gaia Guardian requires four Gaia Pylons and a lit Beacon. The Guardian has a nasty habit of cleansing its foes of potion effects, however is still affected by active flowers. To start the ritual, construct the multiblock found in the Lexica Botania and offer a Terrasteel ingot to the Beacon.

When summoned, the Guardian appears 3 blocks above the beacon, filling its health bar up for 8 seconds, then falling onto the beacon. Hitting the Guardian or entering a 7×7 area around the beacon it will start the first phase.

- The Guardian is immune to fire damage, and cannot take more than 25 damage in a single hit.
- The arena is a sphere with a radius of 12 blocks around the beacon.
- If a player tries to leave the arena, they will be knocked back inside.
- Jumping too high or not being inside the arena might end the fight.

Good Luck

The Charm of Dislocation allows you to teleport from anywhere in any dimension to a specific location for absolutely no cost. However, it can only have one location, and cannot be rebound. Shift+right-click to save the coords, dimension, and direction you are looking. Right click anywhere else to teleport there.

You don't have to look at a block while binding it, otherwise you would be looking straight down when you teleport there. Just look straight ahead, or the direction you want to be looking when you teleport there.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Now That's What I'm Talking About
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
MOAC (Mother of all chests)

This chest has 234 slots and will automatically smelt anything inside of it 5 items at a time. It is also compete with a built-in crafting table and can be picked up while retaining all its contents.

The Essentia Terminal allows you to access Essentia in your ME System. To store Essentia in your ME System, you need Essentia Storage Cells.

The Arcane Crafting Terminal works as a regular Crafting Terminal AND an Arcane Worktable. You put your Wand in there, and craft like normal, but you have access to your entire ME System while doing it.

Without Dimlets, Dimensions are entirely random as far as traits go. Forest biome with multicolored Hardened Clay? Anything can happen. The Dimension Enscriber doesn't require RF, just an Empty Dimension Tab. Put that in, and if you have any Dimlets you want, stick those in too. Click "Store" to make the dimension.

Put the Realized Dimension Tab into the Dimension Builder. Dimensions require a ton of RF to build for the first time, and then a steady supply of RF to keep the dimension enabled. The more complicated or intense the Dimension, the more RF it takes.

In order to customize how your dimension is generated, you use Dimlets. A good source of Unkown Dimlets is a large mob farm. For the most part, Dimlets can go into the Dimension Inscriber in any order. However, Material and Liquid Dimlets MUST go in the slot just before thing they are supposed to modify. For instance, having Large Spheres of Diamond Blocks, you would need to have the Diamond Blocks Material Dimlet in the slot 1 to the left of the Large Spheres Dimlet.

Sometimes you get a bunch of really useless Dimlets that you don't want. You can put 3x into a Dimlet Scrambler and they will be destroyed and give you 1x random Dimlet.

The ME Wireless Access Point and Wireless Terminal allow you to wirelessly access your ME System's items.

The ME Wireless Access Point is the central location that you have to be nearby to in order to use the Wireless Terminal. You can extend the range with Wireless Boosters at the cost of more power usage.

The ME Security Terminal is how you bind your Wireless Terminal to the ME System. Place the Wireless Terminal in the top right and it will bind to that system.

The Wireless Terminal is essentially an ME Access Terminal that you can hold and carry around with you.

If you place a Security Terminal on your ME System, other players won't be able to use the system anymore.

The Essentia Provider allows Thaumcraft machines to access Essentia from your ME System.

The Infusion Provider allows the Infusion Altar to use Essentia from your ME System.

Cursed Earth is created by the activation ritual for the Division Sigil. You can harvest this block with Silk Touch. Cursed Earth will spawn stronger mobs at a high rate. Cursed earth will spread to nearby dirt/grass blocks; however, it will rever back to dirt in sunlight. 

When exposed to light from a non-sunlight source, Cursed Earth will stop spawning mobs. Mobs will spawn even if no player is around. Cursed Earth can be placed under mob spawners to make them work slightly faster and not need players nearby.

Fans "push" entities away from the front of it up to 10 blocks. A redstone signal is required.

Spikes damage mobs that touch them. They will not destory items.

The Cell Workbench can configure each Storage Cell in your ME System to only store items that you tell them to store.

The ME IO Port allows you to transfer items from small cells (such as 4k) to larger cells (such as 64k) very easily.

A View Cell allows you to configure these cells in the Cell Workbench. To use them, craft some separate Terminals, and set a View Cell to only show items that you're searching for frequently. This way, you don't have to search for them all the time, just open the newly crafted Terminal, and they're already there.
Collect the defeated Ender Dragon's Egg.
Laser Drill Fociis are able to "convince" the Laser Drill to only gather specific ores of that category.

As the most advanced of its kind, this conduit is able to transfer an infinite amount of RF per tick. It will connect up to other types of Fluxduct and it can be broken without a tool, but it's broken the fastest by crouching and right-clicking it with a Crescent Hammer, after which it drops to the ground. 'Right-clicking' with a Crescent Hammer or Wrench on a connection will disconnect it, inversely, 'Right click' on the side to be reconnected.

The Magma Crucible uses RF power to melt down items into liquid.

The Fluid Transposer uses RF power to insert/extract fluid to/from specific containers, items, or blocks.

Allows the player to read pop up text displays of items displayed on the different blocks in BiblioCraft.
View the names of books on a bookcase,
View what is on a regular shelf,
View what armor is on an armor stand/display case and what enchantments are on that armor,
Labels become combination item frame/signs displaying the name of the item in them,
The typesetting table displays the name of the selected book as well as the quantity of blank chases left,
The printing press displays the book name of the plate inserted into the press, the quantity of ink, and quantity of blank books left,
The writing desk displays the name of the open book, and
The potion shelf shows the name of the potion the player is looking at.

Max Level: 1
Works on: Helmet

Gives extra yellow-colored hearts that regenerate over time. These hearts are an independent effect, so they stack together with other health-related buffs.

Max Level: 5
Works on: Any Armor

Use the Blood Altar to create some blank slates and a weak blood orb.

The Divination Sigil allows you to see how much LP is in both your network and your altar. Right-click to the altar will show how much it contains, while a right-click elsewhere will show how much is in your personal network.

Equipt a Weak Blood Orb and shift+right-click it to bind it to yourself. This will apply to all Blood Orbs and Activation Crystals. Place your new Blood Orb in the Blood Altar to fill up your own internal Blood Storage. This internal storage is used to cast spells, activate rituals, and craft with the Alchemic Calcinator later on. Alternatively, you can right click the Orb to fill it up a little bit using your own health.

The Magnum Torch denys regular mob spawns in a 64-block range around it.

The Vinculotus Flower uses mana to prevent any Enderman nearby from teleportation anywhere except for directly ontop of the flower. This can be disabled with a redstone signal. Area of effect: 64 blocks?

Upgrade your altar to tier 2 by placing 8x Blood Runes around the block under the altar. (No Blood Rune directly under the Altar).

See link below for Altar construction:
https://ftbwiki.org/Blood_Altar

Using Mutandis on living plants is the only way to obtain certain Witchery plants, like Spanish Moss, Rowan Saplings, Alder Saplings, and Hawthorn Saplings.

Right-click a sapling while holding mutandis will convert the sapling to another living plant. You can keep right-clicking until you get the plant that you want.

The Hydroangea Flower generates Mana from nearby water surce blocks (in a 3x3 area), but has a limited life-span. It will generate more during rain.

The Endoflame Flower is a very powerful early-game mana generating flower that converts any dropped fuel source (such as wood or coal) into mana. It can only generate mana in bursts so do not spam it with fuel.
Drop a steel ingot into the mana pool filled with enough mana (will no longer show an X) to convert steel into manasteel.

Botania's Runic Altar, when provided some mana through mana spreaders, and when the correct materials are applied, it will craft runes for you. To finish each crafting, you need to toss or right-click with a piece of livingrock on the altar, and use your wand of the forest.

Try automating it with automatic mana production, a dropper (or open crate), and a autonomous activator.
Runes of one of the most commonly used crafting materials in Botaina. I highly recommed you try and automate this early on.

Place a spark on one of your Mana Pools and on your Terrestrial Agglomeration Plane to transfer mana to it. Toss (or right-click) a Manasteel Ingot, Mana Diamond and Mana Pearl onto the plate and wait until it creates a Terrasteel Ingot. Each of these ingots requires half a mana pool.

The Greater Ring of Magnetization is an upgrade of the Ring of Magnetization, increasing the affected range from 13x13 to a 33x33 area around the player.


Find a way to automatically create flowers and automatically place them to generate Mana.

Progression in botania goes much further than simple Terrasteel, but contact with the elves will be necessary. Consult the Portal to Alfheim in the Lexica Botania for full instruction on the creation of the multiblock. Additional mana production may be necessary to keep the portal open. Once opened, toss your Lexica Botania through the portal to gain the Elven Knowledge.
No Description
Throwing certain items into the portal will trade with the Elven Dimension and give you new materials back. Check NEI for recipes.
No Description

The Spark is used to transport large amounts of Mana. They can be placed on top of Mana Pools of any type, as well as Terrestrial Agglomeration Plates and Mana Enchanters, by right-clicking them. The Spark entity has a 25x25x25 functional range centered on itself. When a device with a Spark attached needs Mana, it will drain all Mana Pools with Sparks in its range.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Gaia Guardian Boss Fight - HARD MODE
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Defeating the Gaia Guardian is a difficult task; however, you must challenge yourself further to obtain the rarest Botania items. By combining a Terrasteel ingot and a Gaia Spirit, you can create a Gaia Spirit Ingot. By using the Gaia Spirit Ingot in place of a Terrasteel ingot, you can summon a stronger Gaia Guardian. This version of the Gaia Guardian drops more Gaia Spirits as well as unique armor buffs and rare relics.

The Sanity Checker lets you keep track of your current warp levels. When held, it shows a GUI in the top left corner of the screen displaying the varying types of warp the player has. The darkest purple band is permanent warp, while lighter purple is normal (formerly "sticky") warp, and pink is temporary warp. The gold bands represent the required warp levels for the Eldritch Epiphany and Eldritch Revelation. If the meter "overflows", the brain atop it will appear cracked. The more warp you have, the higher your chance of bad things happening to you (such as being attacked by the Eldritch Cult).

Sanitizing soap clears all temporary warp and has a chance of removing some "regular" warp. It will eventually be consumed by use.

The Soul Brazier will store your permanent warp. As long as it has Ignis centi-vis and Mortuus essentia fed from underneath it will stay active, even while you are in other dimensions. Turning it off or running out of power will dump all that warp back into your body, so watch out. Containing warp does have a bit of a downside - taint.

The Wand Recharge Station recharges wands, staffs, scepters, or even a vis amulets, when placed on the pedestal. It will drain primal vis from any/all nodes within 8 blocks in any direction until the item is full. If all available nodes run out of an aspect, the pedestal will continue drawing bits of vis as the nodes regenerate.

The Compound Recharge Focus (no relation to wand foci) can allow the pedestal to drain compound aspects, but it only gets one primal point for each compound point.

Chisel is used to convert normal decoration blocks to different varents of the same block.

The saw is used to cut down blocks into smaller blocks that can be used to make smaller multiblock type structures.
No Description

The Eldritch Eye is the key to enter the Outer Lands. These are obtained from killing Eldritch Guardians that spawn around the worldgen structures or for the player to gain enough warp for Eldritch Guardians to spawn around the player. Four of them need to be placed on an Eldritch Altar and the node must be activated with a wand requiring 100 Vis per aspect to create a portal to the Outer Lands.

Find an Eldritch Obelisk in the overworld. Place 4 Eldritch Eyes on it and activate it with a wand to enter the Eldritch Dimension. This is a huge maze with lots of Thaumcraft mobs to fight. 

Expore the maze and try and locate the Runed Tablet. It serves as a key to the Ancient Doorway that hide the Eldritch Guardian inside.

There is a boss that spawns in the locked room which, when defeated, drops a Primordial Pearl. The pearl can be inserted into a node to set it to have 5 or 6 primal Aspects. It is also a crafting ingredient for several endgame items.
The MFR Block Braker is just like the OpenBlock varient; however, it requires power and is able to break and drop any block it mines.

The Block Breaker is a simple tool for breaking blocks. When the block receives a redstone pulse, it will break the block in front of it, and eject the block to the back of the machine. The OpenBlocks Block Breaker can break anyblock (except bedrock); however, only stone-level blocks will be dropped once broken (blocks such as ores and obsidian will not be dropped).

The Block Placer has 9 inventory slots and will place a block from one of these slots in front of it in the world when it receives a redstone pulse. Any item that can't be placed in front of it in the world will stop the Block Placer from functioning. The slots are emptied from top to bottom and from left to right.

Reapeatable - 1 Week
$1000 to buy a teleportation device that sends the player within several hundred blocks of SpawnTown and has 9 uses. The player is spawned with 4 seconds of Night Vision, 4 seconds of Blindness, 9 seconds of Resistance and 9 seconds of Regeneration IV. These buffs keep the player from seeing where they will land, but keep them from dying upon impact.

This block holds a full set of armor and can be used with or without a GUI.

You can add armor to the stand by holding the piece of armor in your hand and aiming at the desired slot to place the armor, Aim at the top to add a helmet. You can also add/remove/swap armor to and from the stand to and from your inventory by shift+right-clicking on the armor stand on the desired piece of armor/empty slot to add/remove/swap armor to and from the stand.

If a redstone signal is applied to the stand, sneak clicking on the armor stand will swap your entire set of armor. What you are wearing now will be on the stand and what was on the stand will be equipped on your player.

A map is an item used to view explored terrain. When you first create a map, it is blank. Right-clicking the empty map transform the empty map into a map which gradually begins filling with information as you travel around the inside borders of it.

The map frame holds maps and will connect to one another to make large scale connected maps. The map frame can be placed on the floor, wall, or ceiling and the maps in them can be rotated. Using the Drafting Compass, you can add map pins. The map pins can be any of the 16 colors, can be named, and will determine and store the real world coordinates based on the map. The coordinates and pin name can then be retrieved by right-clicking or with the Waypoint Compass.

Maps are added to the map frame by holding a map in your hand and right clicking the map frame with it. Maps can be rotated by shift+right-clicking with an empty hand. Maps can be removed by right-clicking with a screw gun.

The Architect Table is used to 3D scan a structure up to a 64x64x64 area and save a schematic of the structure in a Blueprint. 


A Builder is used to automatically builds structures. Once placed in the world, insert a recorded Template or Blueprint of the structure which was previously saved in an Architect Table.

When a Template or Blueprint is added, the Builder will project a wire-frame cube of black and yellow caution tape, which represents the area that the structure will occupy. Once power is added and the necessary blocks, the builder will start building.


Templates will only store information about the positions of blocks, not the type. While only allowing simple structures using only one block type to be stored in it, any block can be used to rebuild it with a Builder, thus making it possible to rebuild a structure using a different material.

Blueprints are similar to a Template; however, it will also store the material that was used. This allows you to better recreate an existing structure using a Builder.


The Electronic Library is used to store blueprints and templates. When you save something, the design is saved to your hard drive allowing the design to be shared between multiple worlds.

To use a robot:
1. Place the docking station onto a kinesis pipe.
2. Place an emerald gate on the same pipe to program the robot.
3. On the emerald gate, find the output that says "Work in area" and give it a "programmed" Map Location.
4. Set up a condition for the robot to return back to base station once it is out of power or by using a redstone signal.

The Bear Trap, when placed in the world, will trap any mob that walks over the trap if the trap is "set", it will close shut without harming the mob. To open it, a you can simply right-click it.
These items from harvestcraft are used in recipes in most higher-tiered foods. They do not get used up in recipes.

Each farm is made up primarily of Farm Blocks. They must have a Farm Gearbox through which you input RF power. Farm Valve, Farm Hatch and Farm Control blocks are optional, but will be needed if you intend on automating the farm.

All farms will be 4 blocks high and require a platform to work on. The smallest farm will be 3x3x4 with a platform radius of 9, the largest will be 5x5x4 with a platform radius of 15. A 3x5x4 will allow you to have a platform radius of 15 and is generally considered to be the most efficient size farm you can create.

The platform must be built around the sides of the farm. If built on top it will not function.
The Fallen Kanade Flower uses mana to generate an area of effect field of Regeneration III. This flower cannot be turned off with a redstone signal.

The Zone Planner is used to program robot's work area. The upper part shows the map of the world. The brushes in the bottom left corner allow the player to draw areas in different colors on the map. The "+" and "-" buttons allow the player to toggle between "adding new areas" or "removing areas" respectively.

A Map Location is placed in the upper-right slot to save the map area with the coordinates of the drawn area. To edit a Map Location, place it in the middle left slot. The area saved on the Map Location is displayed on the map.

The Gate Copier is used to copy the configurations of a gate to another gate. This can save time when multiple gates require the same or similar configurations.

Right-click to copy the configuration of a gate into the Gate Copier.
Shift+right-click to copy the configuration from the Gate Copier into the gate.

Gates can do all sorts of useful things, such as detecting when an item is traversing the pipe, detecting the state of adjacent machines, interacting with storage containers, etc. When used with Pipe Wires, the possibilities are endless.

Basically gates act as a true/false conditional for hundreds of blocks that are compatible.

Some examples are:
Check if items/power/liquids are traversing through pipe.
Check if chest is empty, full, or has space for items.
Check if tank is empty, full, or has space for liquids.
Check/create a redstone signal.
Check if a machine/engine is working and its current state.

The Filtered Buffer is used to stock and/or count items supplied by pipes and relay the information to a Gate.

Packing Tape is used to move a storage drawer while keeping all of its items.

The Chest Transporter is an upgrade to Packing Tape that can be used to move both chests and drawers.

The Munchdew Flower generates mana by eating leaf blocks (160 Mana per block). It attempts to eat a leaf block every 4 ticks, and checks an area 8 blocks around it horizontally and 16 blocks above. If it cannot find leaves to eat, it goes to sleep for 80 seconds before trying again. Leaves eaten will not drop saplings or other items.

The Narslimmus Flower generates mana by consuming slimes naturally spawned in slime chunks. The flower will consume any natural slime in a 5×5×5 area around it. It will not consume slimes spawned by artificial means. Killed slimes do not drop any items.

The Gourmaryllis Flower generates mana by consuming food items (that do not leave behind containers or byproducts) in a 3×3×3 area around it. The more hunger the food restores, the more mana is produced. The saturation value is ignored. Food items which restore 13 or more hunger will have their value reduced down to 12 hunger.

While the flower is producing mana, any other food items the flower picks up will be destroyed.

The Entropinnyum Flower generates mana by absorbing primed TNT entities in a 12 block range immediately before they explode, producing 6,500 Mana per explosion. It cannot function if it has any Mana stored in its buffer, and cannot absorb TNT entities in liquids.

The Rosa Arcana Flower generates mana by absorbing experience from players standing within 1 block of it. It generates 50 Mana per point of experience absorbed from a player, or 35 Mana per point of experience from an orb, and can store 6000 Mana internally.

The Kekimurus Flower generates a large amount of mana by consuming a cake block.

The flower attempts to consume Cake 1 slice (1/6th) at a time, one slice every 4 seconds (80 ticks). It has a range of 5 blocks. Each slice of Cake eaten produces 1800 Mana (much greater than the equivalent output of a Gourmaryllis would be). A Kekimurus can store 9001 Mana internally, meaning that a single Kekimurus can consume 5/6ths of a Cake without needing to empty its Mana.

The Thermalily Flower generates mana by consuming lava. It searches the same way as a Hydroangeas, all 4 directions and diagonals at the same altitude. After consuming a block of Lava, a Thermalily will produce 20 Mana/tick for 900 ticks (18,000 total), then go on cooldown for 5 minutes.

Horn of the Wild will harvest grass, flowers, and crops in a 25x25x7 area around you (when right-clicked).

Horn of the Canopy will break leaves in a 19x19x15 area around you.

Forn of the Covering will heavest snow layers in a 13x13x23 area around you.

The Mana Tablet is a means to transport Mana in a portable fashion. Dropping one of these on a Mana Pool will allow them to transfer Mana from one to the other, depending on which way Mana is flowing—this can be viewed while looking at a Mana Pool when wielding a Wand of the Forest. Shift+right-clicking with the wand will change the flow of Mana. The Tablet will not despawn when dropped on the ground.

The Band of Mana, when worn in a Baubles shot, is able to store Mana just like the Mana Tablet. The durability bar represents how much Mana has been stored in the Band and not the item's actual durability; another bar can be found above the player's hotbar showing durability in more detail. The band can also be upgraded to the Greater Band of Mana, which can store four times as much Mana.

The Mana Blaster can be used to give blocks and flowers mana and requires the player to have a mana tablet with some mana in it. Right-click to blast some mana at something.

The Vacuum Hopper collects items and XP from a 7×7×7 area around it and transfer them to an adjacent inventory or transport system, such as Itemduct, Fluiduct or Tank. The Hopper has an internal buffer of 10 types of items.

The Floating Flowers are a set of 16 flowers added by Botania. They are a floating variant of Glimmering Flowers and are used primarily for aesthetics and creation of floating variants of all functional Botania flora.

Right-clicking these flowers with a Snowball or any type of Pasture Seeds (including Infestation Spores and Boreal Seeds) will turn the appearance of the flower to match, and will affect the pickup delay of functional ones similarly to normal ones planted on Mycelium or Podzol.

The Auto Workbench will automatically craft an item once the recipe is inserted and resources are pumped in. Items pumped in must be the exact item and not variations of that item (must have same metadata and NBT). This limits the amount of compatible recipes; however, this machine does not require power.

The Advanced Crafting Table allows rapid, automated crafting of a single item provided that the components are in its inventory. It must be powered by a Laser to function.

The Iron Furnace is an upgraded version of the vanilla furnace with faster cooking time.

The Heating Coil is basically a re-chargeable solid fuel to use RF instead of a solid fuel. Most things that requires solid fuel will accept a heating coil. To re-charge the coil, put it in the upgrade slot of an Energy Transfer Node or use an Energetic Infuser.

The Soul Cage functions similar to the vanilla monster spawner, but with some significant differences. It is used with Soul Shards to spawn the mobs that the Soul Shard is bound to and its spawn speed is changed (The speed depends on the tier).

To use a Soul Cage place it in the world, then right-click the cage with a bound Soul Shard. The soul cage will then start spawning mobs as long as the environmental conditions (which are determined by the tier of the Soul Shard) are met. Mob's will start to spawn at a pre-set rate dictated by the Tier of the Soul Shard. If the cage has a Tier 5 Shard then the Soul Cage will then respond to redstone signals, activating the spawner when it is powered.

Whenever you die, you will lose one of your yellow "absorption" hearts. Unlike normal health, absorption levels are fast-regenerating and do not require your hunger level to be full. This allows you to get you back into the fight quickly.

Look at the recipe of the Enchanted Book to see the recipe for the Book of Absorption Having 30 levels of xp and right-clicking the book will gain a heart back. You cannot gain more then then 10 full hearts.

When a player places luggage down, it will start following them around. It will then start eating dropped items around them into their inventory if space is available. Right-clicking will open the inventory and it picks up items from the ground. Shift+right-clicking the luggage entity, it can be turned back into an item and picked up. When picked up, the luggage item will retain all content that's stored in it. Luggage cannot be hurt when in entity form.

Upon being struck by lightning or being blown up by a Charged Creeper, the Luggage will become supercharged, changing its texture, and doubling its inventory space.

The Golden Egg can be placed in the world to create a miniature version of you. They will, basically, walks around, break seeds, flowers, and rearranging items in your chests. They can also pick you up if you get in their way.

They're basically useless just like children in real life.

An elevator allows a player to travel (teleport) between 2 blocks placed up to 20m above or below another elevator block. While standing on the elevator, jump to go up and sneak to go down.

Multiple elevator can be stacked on top of each other to move up or down a large distance.
Ensure no solid blocks are inbetween the elevators.
Only elevators of the same color will allow travel between them.

The Village Highlighter is used to see where the center of a village is, as well as the boundary of the village. When inside of a village, if this block receives a redstone singal, then it will display a yellow box around the center, and a dome of yellow dots around the village.

The yellow dots show the boundary of the village. A village is technically defined as a villager with a roof and a door, and can be expanded by adding more of these. The center of the village is where Iron Golems can spawn. Boundaries can be expanded as more villagers are added, though if a village "house" is too far away from the center, it will be counted as a different village.

The Trading Post displays a list of all the trades available from villagers within a 32x32 area.

The Dry Plain Sponge can absorb up to 3,000 mB of fluid from nearby sources in a 2m radius. The name will change from Dry to Soaked when liquids are retained. The fluid can be extracted using a Fluid Transposer.

The Filing Cabinet is used for storing items that do not stack. The basic Filing Cabinet has 270 item slots and can hold 1,755 items total. All of those items must be of the same type (same item ID) but can have different properties such as damage value or enchantment. The Filing Cabinet keeps the items sorted alphabetically within its interface.

This block can be picked up and will retain its entire inventory.

Examples are: Potions, Enchanted Books, Liquid Drums, and Strongboxes.

The block can be picked up while retaining its full inventory.

The dinner plate is a block that holds up to 3 stacks of food. The food that is placed on the plate can be eaten from the plate with no GUI. The player will consume up to 3 pieces of food (one from each slot) if the player is hungry enough.

The dinner plate can be eating from by right-clicking the plate 4 times. The first 3 clicks are the “chewing” of the food, following by the eating on the 4th.

The cookie jar is a jar for cookies. The jar currently accepts any item and for each slot filled, up to 8, there will appear a cookie in the jar. If mana cookies from Botania mod are placed in the jar, a blue cookie will appear in the jar.

The cookie jar also emits a redstone pulse when the jar is opened. Catch someone with their hand in the cookie jar.

Cookie jars are excluded from use protections meaning anyone can access any cookie jar in the world.

A desk bell will “ding” when right-clicked. Will also “ding” upon receiving a redstone signal.

The whistle will "whistle" when it is used in your inventory.

The shelf can hold up to 4 different stacks of items. Right-clicking the Shelf with any Block or Item will put it on the shelf. Right-clicking an item or block that is on the Shelf will cause that item or block to pop off. Shift+right-clicking with an empty hand will open the GUI.


The tool rack is a block designed to hold up to 4 tools or weapons. Right-clicking the rack with an accepted tool with put the tool on the rack. Right-clicking a tool that is on the rack will cause that tool to pop off. Shift+right-clicking with an empty hand will open the GUI.


The display case is a block that can be placed on the floor or on the wall and holds holds one single item. It has a lid that must be open to obtain the item. Any type of item or block can be placed within the case. 

The case door can be toggled by shift+right-clicking with an empty hand. The case must be open in order to add an item to the case. When the case is open right-click to place an item in the case. Right-clicking while there is an item in the case will cause the item to pop out of the case. 

Placing a redstone block inside a display case will cause the case to emit a redstone signal.

The interior can be colored by right clicking the case with a colored carpet when the case is open. right click the case with the screw gun while the case is open or break the case and it will fall out.


The Bookcase holds up to 16 books and shows visually where the books sits in the inventory. Also works with enchantment tables. Books will be added/subtracted from the slot the player is aiming at. The bookcase can also emit a redstone signal depending on the amount of books poplulated

The Item Translocator is used to transfer items between inventories ONE space apart from each other. Right-clicking the center of the Translocator with an empty hand will toggle between import and export mode, shown by the center piece moving in or out. The Translocators allow up to six inventories to be connected in one space. The GUI can filter up to 9 items.


The Translocator can be upgraded by Right-clicking it with a given upgrade item. Upgrades may be combined. Shift+Right-clicking with an empty hand will remove the upgrades.

Redstone: Makes the translocator respond to a redstone signal.

Iron Ingot: On input mode, it will emit a redstone signal if there is no room for any item that matches the filter. On output mode, it will emit if there is no place where any item can be put that matches the filter.

This upgrade puts the Translocator in Regulate mode. In this mode it will transfer a certain amount of items, set by the filter and mode, to the adjacent inventory. On input mode, it will only accept items to fill the inventory to the matching filter amount. On output mode, it will eject any items above the matching filter amount.

The Rocket needs to be built on your Rocket Assembling Machine, with the Launch Pad blocks delimiting the horizontal space you have and the Structure Tower the vertical space you have (you can't go higher than your stack of Structure Towers and can't go out the rectangle of Launch Pad).

A manned Rocket needs a Guidance Computer, a Seat, at least one Rocket Engine and at least one Liquid Fuel Tank. There are no other restrictions that apply, your Rocket can be as unrealistic as you want so long that you respect the above points.

To check if your Rocket is actually capable of reaching space, go on your Rocket Assembling Machine and click Scan. It will both tell you how what's missing as well as various stats, as follow:
-Thrust: how much thrust the Engines are providing.
-Weight: how heavy is the Rocket.
-Fuel: how much fuel capacity you have, increased by adding more Tanks; the white line is the amount required to reach orbit.
-Acceleration: how fast will the Rocket accelerate on a planet with as much gravity as the Overworld; white bar in the middle is none.

When your Rocket is ready, click Build on the Rocket Assembling Machine. You can then right-click to board it or shift+right-click to open its inventories and check the fuel level.

Finally, insert your Planet ID Chip in the Guidance Computer's inventory, then in the Rocket's inventory click Select Destination, select Luna either on the map or through the Planet List, and click Select.

Make sure you have a full Space Suit filled with Oxygen, then board the Rocket and press Space. You will then arrive on Luna. To go back, select Earth like you selected Luna earlier, board the Rocket and take off again. You don't need as much fuel to take off from Luna.

Once a machine is chosen from the interface described above, you can right-click a spot on the ground to create a hologram of the machine. Holding shift while scrolling with the holo-projector selected will move the cross section of the projected machine in-world.

The chestplate has its own internal oxygen storage which provides 30 minutes of oxygen. The Enhanced Building Guide is used to assist the user in building perfect shapes. When placed and supplied with a Redstone signal, it will place ghost blocks in the world, forming the shape and size defined with the block. The available shapes are: Axes, Cuboid, Cylinder, Dome, Full Cuboid, Hexagon, Octagon, Pentagon, Planes, Sphere, and Triangle. All shapes can be three-dimensional and are dynamic. Using a dye on the Building Guide will turn the guide blocks into the color of the dye, and will not consume the dye. It also allows the placing of actual blocks by right-clicking with any block. Right clicking the up or down arrow on the block's top will change the shape of the guide. This will cycle through all of the available shapes. Clicking on the left or right arrow on the block's top will rotate a shape's direction. Dimensions will display in chat as (-X, -Y, -Z):(X, Y, Z) and are relative to the direction and location of the block's top, where (0,0,0):(0,0,0) is the block itself. The total blocks required is also displayed in chat. The X and Z coordinates change up and down based on the plane the block's side resides on. The Left + and - move along the -X/-Z axis. The Right + and - move along the X/Z axis. The upper + and - move along the Y axis, and the lower + and - moves along the -Y-axis. The internal arrows copy its position to the opposite side. The Hobgoblin is a mob that spawn in forested areas in huts.

Tying them up to force them into servitude with a lead will have hobgoblins pick up loose items on the ground and put them in nearby chests. Giving them a pickaxe when tied up forces them to dig, when digging they are able to find the rare, Koboldite Dust. Koboldite it a material the hobgoblins value very highly and only they can turn the dust into ingots or nuggets.

Note: Experiment with the different pickaxes available. The pickaxe must have the correct mining level to mine that particular ore and tinker's pickaxes do not work.

Hobgoblins are able to be traded with if they are placed in a normal vanilla village. Sometimes you may get lucky with a trade that will give you Koboldite dust from another material.

To respawn the Ender Dragon, travel to The End and build the following structure:

Place the resurrection stone surrounded by Obsidian, with Glowstone blocks in the corners, 1 block down in the ground. Next it has to be surrounded with 4 pillars made out of 1 Pillar Quartz Block and 1 Diamond Block, as well as 4 pillars made out of 2 Pillar Quartz Blocks and 1 Charged Draconium Block. These pillars have to be placed at a maximum range of 5 blocks from the Resurrection Stone. It is important that the ritual be set up within 150 blocks from the 0,0 coordinate of the world.

The ritual is activated by right-clicking the Resurrection Stone once the setup is complete. Right-clicking a second time will cancel the ritual but will still drain all the energy from the Charged Draconium Blocks (they will have to be re-charged).

The new Ender Dragon will have a different texture than the original. It is also harder to and the difficulty increases every time the ritual is performed by the player (up to a certain point). The dragon will also have Regeneration for a short duration once spawned.

Tired of digging miles of tunnels by hand? You've come to the right place. The Tunnel Bore can do it for you.

* Lava suspected.

A Satchel is a portable bag that can store up to 9 stacks of items.

Satchels can have Signalum Security Lock installed on them to configure who may access their contents. They also can be enchanted with "Holding" to increase its storage capacity.

Holding 1: 18 Slots
Holding 2: 27 Slots

Button Upgrade:
Adds buttons to the main inventory which allows you to easily manipulate the items inside and transfer items to/from the backpack.

Damage Bar Upgrade:
Gives a visual representation of how full the backpack is at a quick glance. The specific fullness is calculated as a measure of the entire capacity of the backpack, not just how many slots are full. 

Restocking Upgrade:
Takes items from the backpack and places them in the player's inventory.

Quick Deposit Upgrade:
Shift+right-click on an inventory will attempt to dump all the contents of the backpack into that inventory.

Precise Quick Deposit Upgrade:
Just like the Quick Deposit Upgrade; however, will only dump the items if they already exist in the target inventory.

Large Crafting Upgrade:
Crafts items in a 3x3 grid.
For example, if redstone is specified in the filter it will attempt to turn into redstone blocks when 9 or more are picked up.

Small Crafting Upgrade:
Crafts items in a 2x2 grid.
For example, if sand is specified in the filter it will attempt to turn into sandstone when 4 or more are picked up.

Tiny Crafting Upgrade:
Crafts items by itself (1x1 grid).
For example, if a redstone block is specified in the filter it will attempt to turn into 9 redstone when picked up.

Basic Filter Upgrade:
Adds a list of 9 items you can set that the backpack will automatically pick up.

Advanced Filter Upgrade:
Has 18 slots and has some additional options per item.

Fuzzy Filter Upgrade:
Ignores meta-data of items.

Ore Dictionary Filter Upgrade:
Picks up items of the same ore-dictionary.

Mod Specific Filter Upgrade:
Picks up items of the same modID.

Mining Filter Upgrade:
Picks up items commonly associated with mining.

Void Filter Upgrade:
Deletes any configured items when they are picked up.
