Making a Snow Golem consists placing 2x Snow Blocks on top of each other, and the Pumpkin or Jack-O-Lantern on top.

Snow Golems "melt" in dry/warm biomes or when in contact with rain or water. Unless the golem is effected with a potion of fire resistance.

Snow Golems move towards neutral and hostile mobs and throw snowballs at them up to 10 blocks away. They do not do any damage except to Blazes, but the snowballs will still knock back most mobs that they hit.

Making an Iron Golem consists placing 4x Iron Blocks in a 'T' shape and the Pumpkin or Jack-O-Lantern on top in the center.

Iron golems wander around a village in a patrol-like fashion, staying close to the edges of buildings and other structures. Like villagers, iron golems do not wander away from a village, regardless of how they were spawned.

If not within a village, iron golems slowly wander around, usually making their way to a nearby village.

Iron golems avoid water, lava, fire and cacti. Iron golems are immune to both drowning and fall damage. When in water, they sink, but can still move freely when in and under water.

When provoked, an iron golem moves quickly toward its target and swing its arms up violently to attack, dealing 7-21 hearts of damage and launching the target into the air. Iron golems have a comparatively large attack range.

Iron golems attack most hostile or neutral mobs within 32 blocks of them.

The Cart Assembler is a machine where custom minecarts are configured and built using various Modules.

In order to create or customize your cart you need a hull to attach your desired upgrades to. The wood one can be used for really simple applications; however, I strongly recommend the Standard Hull for starting.

Engines:
Engines power the cart and its modules, enabling the cart to move on its own and perform the functions of its module. A cart may have, at most, three engine modules. During operation, the cart determines which engine to use at a given time according to the Engine Priority.

Tool:
Tools are used for harvesting resources. Only one tool can be added per cart.

Attachments:
Attachments provide additional abilities the cart can perform, such as laying rail, fertilizing crops, or attacking mobs and players.

Storage:
Storage modules function as the cart's inventory when collecting items. With the exception of internal storage, the side that the chests occupy can prevent certain attachments and addons from being built in.

Addons:
Addons are modules that can be added to a cart that perform minor tasks, or work in conjunction with other modules. These include things like melting Snow and Ice for a farm, detecting targets to attack, and controlling the height of a constructed rail line.

Fuel and Assembly:
Once the hull and components are chosen, place any consumable soil fuel into the assembler. Press the 'Assemble' button and the fuel consumption bar will begin to drain as the cart is being built. The progress bar shows the real-time remaining to build the cart.
After you craft side chests you can add more different chests to the cart. Some sides are reserved for tools so no chest can be placed there.
Your cart needs power, obviously. A cart can be powered via coal, solar or lava. Why not power your cart with lava?
Your cart needs power, obviously. A cart can be powered via coal, solar or lava. Why not power your cart with the sun?

The Drill module is used to tunnel into the earth. It will dig through the earth so long as they have track to run on, so it is recommended to include a Railer on board.

The Wood Cutter module will plant one sapling on both sides of the track every second dirt block. It will collect Wood, Saplings, and Apples and place them in a storage module. It can only plant Oak, Birch, Spruce, and Jungle Saplings and will only cut down Wood if it has space for them.

The Basic Farmer module can plant Seeds, Carrots, and Potatoes in a 1 block area on either side of the minecart. Does not keep tilled earth hydrated - this can be accomplished by the Hydrator module.

All tools take up the front slot of the minecart.
Your cart needs power, obviously. A cart can be powered via coal, solar or lava. Why not power your cart with coal?

The sensor has 3 modes:

- Block light is the artificial light emitted from blocks such as torches or lamps
- Hybrid light uses both modes.

The Rain Sensor can sense if rain is falling on it. When it is raining, the sensor will emit a signal through its output. Rain must physically fall on the sensor; however, it is sensitive enough to detect very tiny rain droplets in even the driest of deserts.

The Apiarist Database shows all discovered bees that have been bred in your own Apiary/Alveary. The Apiarist Database keeps track of species, where they live, what they produce, resulting mutations and possible mutations. Possible mutations are only recorded when they are done in your own Apiary/Alveary, and when the recording place is available. The possible and resulting mutations when undiscovered, will tell you if you have the species required to perform the breeding to it or from it.

An Arborist Database shows all of genetic traits, mutations, fruits, and wood products of all tree species discovered by its owner.

The Gene Database lists all genes you have discovered by the type of organism they apply to. To add a gene to an Empty Serum Vial to allow inoculation, the desired gene can be clicked on while holding the vial. An Empty Serum Array can be used to hold more than one gene at once.

The Alveary is a large multiblock hive that suffers no reduction in production that the Bee House or the Apiary has. It will also extend the territory of the bee that is housed inside to double the normal territory radius.

The Alveary can be upgraded with different blocks that change the nature of the multiblock structure. A normal Alveary is a 3x3x3 structure, but you can replace the bottom two layers with different Alveary-compatible blocks, such as a Frame Housing or an Alveary Fan.

To make an Alveary, you will need to place 9x Alveary Blocks on the ground, then another 9x above them, and yet another 9x above that. Cap off the roof with 9x Wood Slabs, and you will see the Alveary change in graphics if done properly.

The Apiary a huge upgrade over the Bee House. It can be automated with Hoppers/Pipes, support frames, and (most importantly) it can allow the mutation of new crossbreed species.


Save the honey you get as a reward for a quest later on where you craft a Beealyzer.

For bees to actually breed and produce honey (and other products), they need a place to live. The Bee House, Apiary, and Alveary are all valid housing for the new Queens and Drones. All of these have their advantages and disadvantages.

For now, however, we will be using the cheapest hive available: the Bee House. While the Bee House can be mass produced easily, it cannot be automated in any way, cannot hold frames, and cannot be used to crossbreed new species. You will need to manually take out the Honeycombs produced, and replace the Princesses and Drones manually. On the other hand, the Bee House extends the lifespan of a queen by three times, only has a 75 percent reduction in production (compared to the Apiary's 90 percent), and makes pollination three times more effective.


Place down 2x Bee Houses and put a Princess and Drone inside the house to convert them into a Queen (don't mix the breeds yet). They will need open air above them, flowers nearby, and a place to work in. Lay down some dirt and put a flower on it.

If everything is correct, the Queen will start working and you'll see tiny bees flying around the hive (means it is working correctly). If it's daytime, not raining, and the hive has no blocks above it, then the Queen will slowly but surely produce honeycombs. At the end of her lifecycle, the Queen will die and produce a Princess and two Drones.

The Isolator creates DNA Sequences using liquid Ethanol and Enzyme together with a subject specimen and Blank Sequence.

A specimen in the Isolator has a chance to be consumed with each operation.

The Analyzer reveals the genome of bees, trees, butterflies, and flowers. It can also be used to reveal the gene present on the DNA Sequence. It requires DNA Dye to stain chromosomes and determine the genome directly.

Any DNA Sequence used in a Sequencer are added to your Gene Database. It requires Fluorescent Dye to function.

The Genepool breaks down bees into Raw DNA for use in other machines by using liquid Ethanol and Enzymes. Different bee types yield differing amounts of Raw DNA. Drones give 10mB, while Princesses and Queens give 30mB.

The Polymerizer takes Serums and refills them using Raw DNA and Replicating Bacteria. The process can be accelerated by using Gold Nuggets.

The 16^3 Spatial Storage is used to store a 16 cubic block space. When used with a Spatial IO Port and Spatial Pylons, the cell will hold a physical area with the dimensions of 16x16x16, or an internal volume of 4,096 blocks.

The 128^3 Spatial Storage is used to store a 128 cubic block space. When used with a Spatial IO Port and Spatial Pylons, the cell will hold a physical area with the dimensions of 128x128x128, or an internal volume of 2,097,152 blocks.

The ME Fluid Assembler works similarly to the Molecular Assembler such that it can craft items that require a bucket of liquid using liquid stored in a ME network, without the need of a bucket or a Fluid Transposer.

The ME Fluid Interface will interface between the ME Network and fluid storage and transport systems, such as Fluiducts, Tanks, and Drums. Each side may be independently configured to a different fluid. The fluid to be exported is set by placing a bucket of that fluid in the empty slot corresponding to that side

The ME Fluid Auto Filler: Whenever a bucket of certain liquid is requested, it automatically fills a bucket from the ME network with the liquid. There needs to be at least 1000 mB of the liquid available in the ME network.

The ME Level Emitter can indicate either the level of a specified item or the ME Network energy level. You can set the threshold and if the ME Level Emitter will emit a redstone signal or turn it off.

The Advanced Inscriber is used to press items using various Inscriber Plates. This one is more automatable though.

Crystal Growth Chamber is used to accelerate the process of purifying crystals, which allows you to create Pure Certus Quartz Crystal, Pure Nether Quartz Crystal, and Pure Fluix Crystal within its GUI.
Component of the Crafting CPU which provides 1,024 bytes of storage for crafting.
Component of the Crafting CPU which provides 4,096 bytes of storage for crafting.
Component of the Crafting CPU which provides 16,384 bytes of storage for crafting.
Component of the Crafting CPU which provides 65,536 bytes of storage for crafting.

The Acceleration Card increases the speed of items being transferred. Also increases power drain while idle.

The Capacity Card increases the number of config slots available.

The Fuzzy Card ignores meta data from items.

The Redstone Card adds the ability to be controlled by redstone signal.

The Inverter Card changes the standard whitelist into a blacklist.

The Crafting Card requests auto-crafting from the system.

You can find flowers from Botania growing on the ground. Collect them and turn them into mystical petals. You are probably going to want to stack up on a bunch of these.

Many recipes from Botania require these Petals.
Produces mana by eating Dayblooms, Nightshades, and Hydroangeas Flowers.
Produces mana by eating colored wool.

The Dandelifeon is probably the strongest flower available but it is the most confusing to put to work.

When a redstone signal is applied to the flower, it will advance one generation 10 ticks. Each square in the 25x25 area is referred to as a cell. Cells can have two possible states:
- Live: the cell has a Cellular Block above it.
- Dead: the cell does not have a Cellular Block above it.

The state of a cell will change depending on the states of its neighbors (which are the 8 squares surrounding the cell):
- Live > Dead: The live cell has fewer than two or more than three live neighbours.
- Live > Live: The live cell has exactly two or three live neighbours.
- Dead > Live: The dead cell has exactly three live neighbours.
All transitions occur simultaneously.

Botania has some additional rules over the original Game of Life:
- Age: each live cell will have an age value attached to it. For each generation the cell will have its age increased by 1. When a dead cell becomes a live cell, its new age is A_{new\ cell}=neighbour_{oldest}+1.
- Mana conversion: the 3x3 area centered on the Dandelifeon is uninhabitable by cells. Any cells that grow into that area will be converted into Mana, and all other cells in the Dandelifeon's range will die. The age of a cell is directly proportional to the Mana it produces. Age 0 cells will not generate Mana, age 101 and older cells will generate as much Mana as age 100 cells.
- Multiple Dandelifeons: a cell that is in the functional range of at least 2 Dandelifeons will die and cannot be turned into a live one.
- Means of Transport: Cellular blocks that are moved by other means than the Dandelifeon will break and cannot be recovered.
- Cell Occupation: Cellular blocks will not generate on cells that are already occupied by non-air blocks.

The amount of generated Mana per consumed cell is equal to Age*60 (for example, the maximum amount of Mana generated by the flower at once is 6*100*60 = 36000 mana.
The Tigerseye Flower uses mana to prevent creepers within range from exploding. Creepers affected by this flower will run away from players.
The Bubbel Flower uses mana to create a sphere of air with an 11 block radius around it. This air replaces water; however, once the flower stops working, water will return into the area.
The Tangleberrie Flower uses mana to keep mobs and animals within a circle with a radius of 5 blocks.
The Heisei Dream Flower uses mana to turn hostile mobs against eachother, with a range of 5 blocks. It will continue to use mana to apply this effect even if no mobs are present nearby.

The Spectranthemum Flower uses mana to teleport items dropped nearby to a bound block within a 12 block range. This only works for items that do not contain mana, and items can only be teleported using this flower once. The flower will not interact with items teleported by any other Spectranthemum. This can be disabled with a redstone signal.
The Exoflame Flower uses mana to power coal burning machines that are close to it.
The Medumone Flower uses mana to apply an extreme Slowness effect to any mobs in its vicinity. This does not affect players and can be disabled with a redstone signal.
The Jaded Amaranthus Flower uses mana to quickly grow mystical flowers in a 9x9 space around it on grass and dirt blocks.
The Clayconia Flower uses mana to convert Sand Blocks (placed within a range of 5 blocks) into a Clay Ball.
The Dreadthorne Flower uses mana to inflict damage on mobs in its vicinity. It will only damage adult animals, no baby mobs will be hurt. This can be disabled with a redstone signal.

The Orechid Flower turns nearby Stone into ores. To do this, the Orechid must be bound to a nearby Mana Pool and will consume a large amount of mana per operation. Each ore generated is selected at random, with the likelihood of each ore appearing being affected by the frequency with which they spawn naturally in the world. The Orechid can be disabled by applying a redstone signal. Operating range of Orechid is 5x5x2 around the flower.

The Orechid Ignem Flower functions similarly to The Orechid Flower; however, it only functions in the Nether, where it transforms Netherrack blocks into Nether Ores.
The Hyacidus Flower uses mana to apply a poison effect to any mobs in its vicinity. This does not affect players and can be disabled with a redstone signal.

The Pollidisiac Flower uses mana to provide valid food items from an adjacent inventory to any passive mobs in the vicinity that will accept feeding. It does not change any of the usual passive mob breeding or growth mechanics.

The Agricarnation Flower uses mana to speed up crop growth by randomly applying a bonemeal effect to crops planted nearby, with a range of 5 blocks. It will continue to use mana to apply this effect even after crops are fully grown. This can be disabled with a redstone signal.

The Rannuncarpus Flower will pick up and place any block dropped close by it. It does not require mana to function, though its range can be increased by providing it with mana. The flower will only place blocks on the material directly underneath the dirt block it is planted on, allowing the player to specify where blocks are set. It can be disabled at will by applying a redstone signal.

The Hopperhock Flower takes items dropped in the world around it and places them in an adjacent inventory. It does not require mana to do this, but supplying mana will increase the range of the flower.
The Solegnolia Flower disables the Ring of Magnetization in radius of 4 blocks and doesn't require Mana. This can be disabled with a redstone signal.
HIDDEN QUEST

The Daffomill Flower uses mana to push items in whichever direction the face is oriented. The direction the flower is facing can be changed by shift+right-clicking with Wand of the Forest. This can be disabled with a redstone signal.

The Manual - Witchery (Circle Magic), describes all of the rites that a player may create. Each page in the book describes the rite, the foci items, power and circles that are needed.

Rite of Binding
Binds something to an item (the circles, the location, etc).

Rite of Charging
Charges an item or the player.

Rite of Glyphic Transformation
Changes the type of glyphs in one of the circles around the ritual.

Rite of Infusion
Infuses an infusion into a player or item.

Rite of Summoning
Summons spectral and infernal beings.

Rite of Protection
Creates an impenetrable dome.

Rite of Imprisonment
Prevents creatures leaving the circle.

Rite of Sanctity
Prevents creatures entering the circle.

Rite of Icy Expansion
Causes a large sphere of ice to expand outwards.

Rite of Broken Earth
Causes the earth to rupture; creating a fissure in a defined direction.

Rite of Moving Earth
Raises a column of earth.

Rite of Earth's Wrath
Causes a volcano to erupt.

Rite of Sky's Wrath
Causes a thunderstorm after a lot of focused lightning.

Rite of Broiling
Cooks food placed in the circle. May overcook some of it.

Rite of Transposition
Teleports players, creatures, and items in various ways.

Rite of Manifestation
Allows a player to manifest as a ghost by passing through Spirit Portals in the Spirit World.

Rite of Beastial Call
Transposes animals from a wide area around to the heart glyph.

Rite of Total Eclipse
Causes nighttime to descend.

Rite of Necromancy
Create a Necromantic Stone to control raised undead .

Rite of Banishing
Sends demons back whence they came.

Rite of Fertility
Makes land in a wide are receive a dose of bone meal; heals zombie villagers and players.

Rite of Nature's Power
Terraforms the immediate vicinity; turning desert and caves into grottoes.

Rite of the Forest
Grows a forest at the target location based on the sapling used.

Rite of Shifting Seasons
Changes the biome and can cause snow or melting.

Rite of Remove Curse
Removes a Curse of Misfortune; has a chance to make things worse.

Curse of Misfortune
Causes periodic random effects to inflict the victim, can only be removed with magic.

Curse of Insanity
Causes the victim to see and hear imaginary monsters.

Curse of Sinking
Causes the victim to sink faster and surface slower in water.

Curse of Overheating
Causes the victim to occasionally catch fire in hot places.

Curse of Waking Nightmare
Cuases the victim to be visited by their nightmares.

Curse of Corrupt Poppet
Destroys Voodoo protection poppets bound to the victim.

Curse of Blindness
Blinds creatures and players in a wide area.

Curse of Blight
Kills plants and animals, infects villagers, causes nausea in players.

Curse of Hell on Earth
Allows creatures from the nether to pour into the overworld.

Curse of Raining Toads
Causes toads to rain down and explode into a poisonous fog.

Curse of the Wolf
Causes a player of Villager to contract lycanthropy.

The Jiyuulia Flower uses mana to create a magical force field around itself, keeping all mobs away. It can be compared to the Magnum Torch from Extra Utilities, but at lower production cost and a smaller protection field.

The Marimorphosis Flower uses mana to turn stone in its vicinity into Metamorphic Stone. The variant of Metamorphic Stone produced is mostly random and all variants are possible, but the chance to get each type is weighted by the biome the flower is placed in.
The Bellethorne Flower uses mana to inflict damage on all living mobs within range. This does not include players and it can be disabled with a redstone signal.

The Floral Obedience Stick will bind all nearby flowers to a single block.

The Manastar Flower displays whether adjacent Mana Pools are operating on a profit or on a loss of mana. It does not require mana to do this. It will give a red particle effect when it detects a loss and a blue particle effect when it detects an increase. This is especially useful when managing large mana networks.

The Manaseer Monocle allows you to see the range on all Botania flowers and machines.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Pinch Me, I Must Be Dreaming
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The spirit world is an alternate reality that mirrors the Overworld in topography. When people dream they often end up in the spirit world without realizing it. Powerful witches can create Brews of Sleeping that allow them to pass their awake consciousness into the Spirit World, leaving their bodies and gear behind.

The Spirit World is the only source of Wispy Cotton, Disturbed Cotton, Mellifluous Hunger (the materials needed to make Dream Weavers). Also Brews of Flowing Spirit can only be made in the Spirit World, circle magic does not function, and Endermen cannot enter the Spirit World.

Very few things can pass into, or return from the Spirit World, keep this in mind when heading there Icy Needles. Wispy Cotton, Disturbed Cotton, Mellifluous Hunger, and Brews of Flowing Spirit can pass from the Spirit World to the Real World but not the other way (excluding Icy Needles).

When a witch enters the Spirit World they will either experience a Dream or a Nightmare. Visitors experiencing a nightmare will additionally be chased by a physical embodiment of their Nightmare. To reduce the chances of a nightmare one can place a Dream Weaver of Nightmares nearby before Sleeping. Having a pool of flowing spirit and Wispy Cotton nearby also helps.

Eating an Apple of Sleeping will also allow entry to the Spirit World, but it will always result in a nightmare.

When a witch enters the spirit world, almost all of their gear will stay behind, being restored when they awaken.

A witch will always return from the Spirit World when they die (without consequence), they may also return earlier by using an Icy Needle on themselves to wake up. Gear from the spirit world will stay there, being replaced by thier normal gear when they awaken. If the sleeping body of a witch is killed, this will also force the witch to awaken.

The Osmotic Enchanter allows you to choose the type of enchantment you want to be enchanted on an item. Instead of using experience, vis from your wand will be used to enchant the item. The wand must have a golden cap or better for the Enchanter to function. When set up, the player places their wand and the object they would like to enchant into the spaces on the GUI. They will get many options for enchanting each with base costs in vis. These will be drained from the wand when the enchantment is started.

In order to use the Osmotic Enchanter, there must be 6 pillars within 4 blocks of the Osmotic Enchanter. The Pillars needs to made from Obsidian Totem blocks, 2-12 blocks high. A piece of Nitor is required on top of each pillar.

The following quests are in categories of all the "Agricraftable" seeds you can collect in this pack.

I highly recommend you make a build to automate any seed you input all the way to 10x10x10 automatically. Otherwise, this could take a while.

Note: There are 4 pages to this quest.
Scroll with the bottom right-side arrows.

Mine Biome Essence Ore in the End to get Biome Essence of a random biome.

Activate the Biome Radar by crafting it with a Biome Essence attuned to a specific biome. Then, right-click the radar to start searching for the biome. It may not be the closest biome.

Note: For this quest, it does not have to be ForestHills essence. It can be any type.
A Exotic Flower Band is an upgraded version of the Lush Flower Band. When wearing this band as a helmet, passive mobs will follow you as though you are carrying food.

The Flügel Tiara gives the player creative flight by consuming small amounts of Mana from a carried Mana Tablet. When in flight, white sparks trail behind the player.

The flight is not infinite. It does have a cooldown that the player will have to wait to charge up again.

The RF Meter is the block form of the Multimeter, with some OpenComputers magic built in.

With no computer attached to the Meter, it measures the total flow of energy and the average flow per second. Shift+right-clicking with an empty hand changes the direction of energy flow.

- Connecting it to an Open Computer enables much more functionalities.
- The Meter stores its values when picked up and can be zeroed out by putting it through a crafting grid.
- Right-clicking the Meter with a dye changes the display color.
- When using Buildcraft Pipes you need the pulling kinesis pipe (Wood or Emerald) on the output end of the Meter.

The Variable Redstone Emitter gives off a configurable vanilla redstone signal of a given strength (0 to 15) to one of its sides. Use the handy table below to lookup diodes and values (1 is ON, 0 is OFF).

The Portable Scanner has two functions. The first is if you right-click a non-simple block, it will provide you with some information regarding it's properties. The second is that while the scanner is selected it will show you a representation of the movement of items and fluids through a transfer pipe system.

The Glove works the same as an Empty hand when you left/right-click on a block. Any items placed into your hand as a result of clicking will be added to the inventory or dropped on the ground if the inventory is full. Use different colors of wool to make different colors of gloves.

Sickles are tools that can be used to break large amounts of plant-like blocks at once. When a plant-like block is broken with a sickle, up to 49 plant-like blocks in a 7x7 area around it are broken as well. This also works on cobwebs. When sneaking, a sickle breaks only one block.

Overgrowth seeds can be used to create enchanted soil. This special soil speeds up the production of botania plants that are grown ontop of it. It cannot be moved even with silk touch, so be careful where you place it.

betterquesting:10.name:8: I Like to Move it Move it
betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Golden Lasso is used to capture passive mobs. Right-click on a mob to capture it and place it down again by Right-clicking on the ground with the same lasso. Mobs captured in the lasso can be renamed by renaming the lasso in an Anvil (Except Villagers). It can also be placed alone in a crafting grid to give it a random name.

The Woodworker creates Patterned Wood Blocks from Wood Planks. Most Wood Planks can be used as materials. Wood Polish is required as an adhesive to create the blocks.

The Panelworker creates Patterned Wood Panels from Wood Planks. Most Wood Planks can be used as materials. Wood Polish is required as an adhesive to create the blocks.

The Glassworker creates Patterned Glass Blocks from Glass Blocks. Most Glass Blocks can be used as materials. Glass Fittings are required as an adhesive to create the blocks.

The Tileworker creates Patterned Ceramic Blocks from Ceramic Blocks. Any of the 80 Ceramic Tiles can be used as materials. Mortar is required as an adhesive to create the blocks.

The Matter Condenser compresses items into a special type of energy. Energy can be stored on ME Storage Components (1k - 16384k). It has three functions:
- Elimination of excess materials into the void.
- Production Matter Balls from 256 Items.
- Production of Singularities from 256,000 Items.

A 64k ME Storage Component is needed to create a Singularity. After one is created, throw it down along with a piece of Ender Dust and blow up TNT next to it. This will create 2x Quantum Entangled Singularities that will be used in the next quest to teleport items over long distances.

You might consider renaming your Quantum Entangled Singularity to better identify the connection.

A Quantum Network Bridge is a multiblock structure that connects 2x potentially distant ME network fragments together. 8x ME Quantum Rings placed around a ME Quantum Link Chamber will create a Quantum Network Bridge. Only the four ME Quantum Ring Blocks adjacent to the ME Quantum Link Chamber will accept network connections, the four corner blocks cannot connect to cables. You will need to create 2 of these structures ...obviously.

Each Quantum Network Bridge requires power to function. This power must be provided from the network fragment it is attached to until the bridge is linked; at which time power from either side will be available. However if power is lost, connectivity will fail and power will be drained from the side the bridge is on in attempt to restore connection.

To establish a link between 2 Quantum Network Bridges, you must create a pair of Quantum Entangled Singularity. One of each will be placed inside of a particular connection. Each Bridge may only connect to one other bridge.

You might consider renaming your Quantum Entangled Singularity to better identify the connection.

Checklist:
- Both sides of the Quantum Network Bridge powered. The lights turn on if they are.
- A matching pair of Quantum Entangled Singularity in each bridge.
- Both sides must be chunkloaded.
- Make sure you only have 1 controller; the other side of the bridge is still the same network.
- Power and network connectivity must connect to the four edges, not the four corners.

P2P Tunnel (or Point-to-Point Tunnels) are a versatile configurable system to move items, redstone, power, and fluids from one location to another though an existing ME Network without the items, fluids, etc. ever actually entering the ME Network itself (it simple passes through it).

Tunnels are 1 input to N outputs. This means you can output to as many points as you want, but only input at a single point per tunnel. Networks can support any number of tunnels, of any different types, and they all function independently.

ME Tunnels can be used to carry channels from one location to another, and can carry up to 32 channels, same as a ME Dense Cable, while only requiring a single channel per point, making tunnels a very powerful tool to expand me networks, especially over a distance. However with the great flexibility they give you comes a limitation, the channel of a p2p tunnel cannot be carried by another p2p tunnel, meaning that you cannot nest them recursively.

To configure a P2P Tunnel you must first attune the tunnel to carry what you want it to, then you need to configure the outputs to their input. You configure the connections by using the Memory Card; First shift+right-click the input to save it on your memory card, then simply right-click the different outputs to store the input onto the outputs. this also sets the type of the output to match the type of the input.

Tunnels can be attuned by right-clicking on them with different types of items:
- ME Tunnel (Light Blue Color)
  Any ME Cable

- Item Tunnel (Dark Gray Color)
  Buildcraft Item Pipes
  ME Export Bus
  ME Import Bus
  ME Interface
  ME Chest
  Hopper

- Fluid Tunnel (Dark Blue Color)
  Any Liquid Containers (IE buckets)
  Buildcraft Liquid Pipes

- Light Tunnel (White Color)
  Glowstone Block
  Torch

- Redstone Tunnel (Red Color)
  Redstone Dust
  Repeaters
  Comparator

- RF Tunnel (Light Gray Color)
  Extra Utilities Energy Pipes
  Thermal Dynamics Fluxducts
  Buildcraft Kinesis Pipes
The Item Dislocator is an upgraded version of the Botania Magnet Ring that instantly picks up items.

Summoning Demons in Blood Magic requires that the Player build a particular layout of Arcane Pedestals surrounding an Arcane Plinth and place certain ingredients atop the pedestals with a Master Blood Orb on the Plinth. When done correctly, the ingredients will be consumed — except the Blood Orb — and a Demon will be summoned.

https://ftbwiki.org/Summoning
Autocraft each of these ingredients so you never run out.

Bound Armor is a powerful suit of armor. It takes a significant amount of Life Essence to create and use, but makes the wearer nearly invulnerable.

The Soul Armor Forge has no interface. Placing Filled Socket Blocks in the world along with the Forge. The shapes to create pieces of armor are the same as the shapes for vanilla armor in the crafting table.

Once the appropriate pattern is created, right-click on the Forge (no Weak Activation Crystal needed). This will combine the blocks into the respective piece of armor.

Create a full set of Bound Tools. You need to set up the binding ritual to convert the Thaumcraft tool into the Bound Tool.

The Bound Blade is able to get Crystallized Souls from your enemies.

The Convocation of the Damned is a ritual that creates a Demon Portal, which will over time create a city filled with Demon Grunts. These demons are the only way to obtain Soul Shards and Life Shards both of which are required to progress to Tier 6 in Blood Magic.

Building the Convocation of the Damned requires a Master Ritual Stone, 128 Ritual Stones. Activation requires 15,000,000 Life Essence. Additionally, it also requires 8 Crystal Belljars, filled in turn with Magicales, Potentia, Incendium, Terrae, Tenebrae, Sanctus, Aether and Aquasalus, need to be present on top of the 8 inner pillars of the ritual before the ritual will trigger, and a Blood Altar needs to be placed on the Master Ritual Stone.

Once the ritual has been activated, the Master Ritual Stone must be empowered with 16,000 AR of each of the above reagents to prime the ritual.

Finally, once primed (the lightning show has finished and all the crystal bell jars are empty) a Demon must be sacrificed within range of a Blood Altar that has been placed on the Master Ritual Stone using a Dagger of Sacrifice. This will create the Demon Portal and convert the inner area of the ritual into an incomplete blood altar, destroying the Crystal Belljars and most of the Ritual Stones.

The Alchemic Calcinator converts one reagent into 1,000 AR, consuming 2,000 LP in the process. The produced AR flows into the internal buffer of 2,000 AR, from where it slowly goes into the 4,000 AR main tank. The main tank will output to a single target container. This can be disabled by applying a Redstone signal. To insert an orb or a reagent simply Right-click the Calcinator with it. An orb must be first inserted in order to activate it.

The Calcinator needs to be hooked up to a target container such as a Crystal Belljar in order to transfer AR, set the destination using an Alchemic Router. To clear already set destinations use an Alchemic Cleanser.
Scepters have a much larger capacity and vis discount than regular wands; however, they are unable to hold any foci.

The Advanced Alchemical Furnace is a multiblock structure. Like Alchemical Furnace, it can smelt items into Essentia. But this furnace requires no solid fuel; only Ignis vis to keep heat and Aqua and Perditio vis during the smelting process. Items to be smelted can be thrown directly in the center of the machine from above. The Essentia can be output from the bottom center block on any side.

After construction, the structure must be activated with a wand containing 50 Aqua, 50 Ignis, and 50 Ordo.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Ichorium Adorned Ichorcloth Strapped Silverwood Wand
betterquesting:10.desc:8: This wand holds 1,000 of each aspect.

The Death Protection Poppet will redirect the death (irrespective of cause) of the bound player or creature to the poppet, destroying it in the process. This poppet is the only way to prevent certain types of death. The poppet will also give a short buff against the cause of death and heal a bit of life, allowing the player a small amount of breathing space to get out of trouble.

For this effect to occur, the poppet must either remain on the protected being or be stored on a poppet shelf somewhere.

Obtain a companion through Circle Magic. Then, talk to 6 Witches around the map and ask them to join your Coven. Once you've completed all six of their quests, create a Seer Stone (Circle Magic page 65) to be able to call them on demand.
Create a Wolf Altar then transform yourself into a Werewolf using the Curse of the Wolf (Circle Magic page 81). Start questing and upgrade your Werewolf level with the Wolf Altar.

READ THIS:

https://ftb.gamepedia.com/Draconic_Evolution_Reactor_Guide

The Charged Porter, when linked to a Matter Receiver, allows you to teleport to it instantly. The further away a player is, the more power it consumes. Teleporting from another dimension uses almost all of the power.
The Advanced Charged Porter is an upgraded version of the Charged Porter that holds more power.
This wand holds 250 of each aspect.

There's nothing more frustrating than having to pause your research to refill your inkwell. Sometimes you're just so desperate to complete a research that you would rather use your own blood as ink.

The Bloody Scrivener's Tools will refill using Life Points from the owner's own network at a rate of 25 LP/point. You will have to remove the tool from the research table first; however, it is still quicker than refilling by other means.
Best of the best

The Cargo Manager allows minecarts load and unload items. It works in conjunction with the Advanced Detector Rail. Minecarts will always stop at the Advanced Detector Rail and process items according to the settings in the Cargo Manager.

The Cargo Manager has four color coded sides, each indicated by the colored square in the lower left corner of the panel. Minecarts that stop on an Advanced Detector Rail next to one of the colors will only process items in the section of the Cargo Manager that have the same color. In the image to the right, a minecart that stops on the green side will only process items in the Cargo Manager that are coded green.
While the nodes across the world are extremely useful for vis and research, they are not always in the most ideal location. Perhaps some additional research will allow you to a mobile alternative.

Nine Hells
Summons firebats to harass and eventually blast your target.

Portable Hole
Produces a short-lived tunnel reaching into the surface you zap it at. Despite appearances, you can walk on the starry edges of the hole; however, be warned, if you are inside when the effect expires, you will be buried alive.

Warding
Makes solid/opaque blocks unbreakable and indestructible to anyone but the player who warded them.

Dislocation
Can hold a block or a tile entity and place it somewhere else while retaining its current state. Transporting tile entities increases the cost 5x and Mob Spawners 20x.

Ender Rift
Will open the player's Ender Chest inventory. It can be set to use the Ender Chest added by EnderStorage by Shift+right-clicking on one.

Telekinesis
Can move nearby dropped items where you are pointing with the wand. It will move them towards you if you hold Shift.

Excavation
Shoots a green beam of light that has a range of 10 blocks and will mine and collect any block it is pointed towards like a normal pickaxe would. It will not mine normally indestructible blocks.

Efreet's Flame
Will smelt any block that can be smelted in a furnace with the output of it also being a block (ex: sand into glass).

Repeatable - Instant
$20 to buy a manual that can be crafted into any other manual using cobblestone.
No Description
Another good way of tripling your ore output is using a pickaxe of the core.

Wood Tracks are functionally equivalent to normal tracks, but with a lower maximum speed (for safety reasons). These tracks are able to be crafted without the need for any machines.

Hint: You can use your Wood Tracks for Steve's Carts farms.
If you decide to not use a locomotive and drive with one or two carts only, you can use some Booster Tracks. Use a redstone signal to power them.

If you plan to automate the fluid transport from, lets say, your Oil field far away, you need a Fluid Loader and a Fluid Unloader. A locking track will stop the train while fluid is being loaded or unloaded (as long as you configure it properly).

An Anchor Cart keeps chunks near the cart loaded in memory. It is very useful for trains that run long distance without a player nearby (such as one that transports oil to your base). Just like normal World Anchors, they require $1 for every 2 hours of operation.

The Electric Track is designed to move Electric Locomotives. Technically, normal carts can move on it, but it isn't conventional.

They are meant to be placed on Wire Support Frames with Electric Shunting Wires, so that they can receive their required energy, so they can give energy to the locomotive, so you can move, so you can probably die (cause you suck at this game).

Did you ever dream of driving in a minecart at high speeds? Well your dreams can come true with the high speed tracks. Be careful though; you need to lower the speed when your rails change direction or when the track ends, or else...
Railroads in the nether are dangerous and Reinforced Tracks are blast proof. Hope you are blast proof too. You can move 25% faster than normal tracks.

The Switch Lever is the manual version of the Switch Motor, requiring a player to operate it instead of a redstone signal.  It is used in various signaling systems, mainly to change the way switch tracks and wye tracks work.

The Junction, Wye, and Switch Tracks allow you to join and switch to tracks going in different directions using the Switch Lever

The Crowbar is used to manipulate machines from Railcraft as well as breaking certain objects faster, such as tracks. This tool is also used to access certain inventories from Railcraft.

Hold a crowbar and shift+right-click to attach carts. Click the starting cart then continue to click to add more carts to the link. Carts will act slower the more connections are made.

The crowbar can be used as a weapon, though it costs twice as much durability on attack.

Minecarts can be ridden by pressing right-click to board them. Once inside, an external impulse may be needed to make the minecart start moving. The player can slowly move the minecart forwards while riding it, by pressing forward. If a mob walks in front of an empty minecart, it will be pulled into the cart.

Players can exit the minecart by pressing Shift. After rolling off of the end of a track, a minecart can be pushed around on open blocks. If a minecart is pushed onto or falls onto tracks, it will "snap" to those tracks.

The Steam Locomotive is much better than the Furnace Cart. You can control the speed and the direction the Locomotive will move. You need to put Water and a solid fuel inside to make steam to power it.

The Bounce Pad sends any entity or player vaulting in the direction indicated by the mark on the Bounce Pad's side. If put above one another the pads' bounce boosts multiply and the bounce gets higher.

The Bounce pad can also be set to launch to a corner (can be seen by the little blue slime chunk on the pad) and launches anything.
The wireless booster is used to increase the range of the ME wireless access point.

The Alchemic Chemistry Set is used to craft a bunch of items in Blood Magic.

To create an item, place the ingredients in the five slots surrounding the middle and a Blood Orb in the lower right slot. Some recipes require higher tier orbs than others. The output will be placed into the middle slot. The chemistry set will drain Life Essence from the Soul Network and produce the item. While it is operating, it will emit red particles. To make the blood orb functional, you must right-click to drain your life, similar to when using a sacrificial orb and a blood altar.

Regular glass phials are unable to hold these special potions you want. You need to imbue them with some blood from your altar.

In order to manipulate potions you need catalysts. You then combine the ingredient you used to get the potion effect in with either a lengthening or power catalyst to increase the duration or the strength of the potion effect.

Different types of potions are crafted by combining Potion Flasks and Weak Binding Agents/Standard Binding Agents and different ingredients (listed below) in the Alchemic Chemistry Set.

Several effects can be added to a potion, but the more effects a potion has the less chance of success. And in case of failure, the potion will explode. Chances of success are calculated by the formulas: 0.4^X (Weak Binding Agent) and 0.65^X (Standard Binding Agent). Where X is the number of effects in the potion before adding a new one.

The current effects of the potion can be powered up by a catalyst. Power catalysts: Mundane, Average, and Greater give better levels of effects, but decreases its duration. Lengthening catalysts: Mundane, Average, and Greater increases the potion's duration.

Once empty, you don't have to throw the potion away. Just refill it using the Weak Refill Agent.

The Scoop allows the player to collect bees from hives. To collect bees, hives must be broken with a scoop, otherwise no bees will be collected.


§eNote: The drones can be any drone, not just forest.

The Centrifuge is an invaluable asset. When powered, it will grind up your honeycombs into both beeswax and honey drops. Different combs will have different outputs. The honeycombs themselves will only give a honey drop 90 percent of the time, so you may not get one if you're unlucky.

The Beealyzer is the most important tool a new apiarist can have. It  will tell you the exact stats of a bee.

By placing Honey Drops or Honeydew in the upper right slot and a bee (Queen, Princess, or Drone) in the slot below it, the bee will be analyzed and placed in the I slot.
-I slot shows the primary stats of a bee.
-II slot shows the biome requirements and secondary stats.
-III slot shows the possible produce and the specialty produce,
-IV slot shows if the bee can be further mutated, and will keep track of what bees you have analyzed (question marks represent combinations that have not been discovered yet).
-V is simply lore and fluff.

Analyzing the bee will also give detailed tooltip information when you hold Shift while hovering over the bee. Note, however, that analyzing the bee will make it stackable only with other bees of the same type that have been analyzed too.

-

By powering the Squeezer and placing either Honey Drops or Honeydew inside, you will produce Liquid Honey. Sometimes (5 percent chance) a Propolis will be produced as well. These will be used later for making certain items. Seed Oil can be produced by placing a variety of seeds or nuts (and some fruits) inside the Squeezer.

Wax Capsules are stackable one-use buckets that can hold non-heated liquids such as honey or water. They will not be able to hold lava. For that, you will need a special type of wax.

If there is a tiny bit of liquid left in the Squeezer and you need to produce a new liquid, you can either:
-Break the machine with a Pickaxe and replace it; or
-Use a Pipette to clear it; or
-Just have one Squeezer per liquid (duhh......)

The Moistener can turn Wheat and Seeds into, Mulch, Mycelium, and Mossy Stones. It requires NO power, but it will only work in darkness (either a dark room or at night).

Mycelium will allow you to plant Mushrooms for the flower requirements of certain bees. Mushrooms normally will break when exposed to light, but Mycelium acts as a guard, allowing the Mushrooms to stay where they are even at high noon.

The Carpenter is used to craft specific recipes. Right now, the only thing you should be interested in is making Impregnated Casings. These casings will allow you to make the Apiary, an upgraded version of the Bee House. The Apiary can also allow crossbreeding to get new species, which is what you want right now. You're sick and tired of breeding Meadows and Forest Bees, right?

The upper-left grid of the Carpenter is where you will set your recipe. The lower grid is where you will store the items required in the recipe, and the tank slot on the right will hold liquids necessary for crafting.

§aUsing a Carpenter to craft Rail Ties is more efficient and much easier.§r

The Splicer is an advanced version of the Inoculator that allows the injection of genes from Serums into individuals. Like the Inoculator, these must be larvae (butterflies), pollen (trees and flowers) or serums (bees).

The Splicer does not require liquid Bacteria Vector and it works much faster; however, it requires much more energy. The machine takes 1 minute to do one gene, with an additional 30 seconds for each additional gene. It will only add genes that aren't already present.

The Basic Logistics Pipe is a central part of the Logistics Pipes mod. Besides being used to craft any other Logistics Pipe, they also provide full routing functionality in a logistics system. They can also act as a destination for up to nine different items, or as a default route for items that do not have any other destination.

Basic Logistics Pipes are also necessary to connect a logistics system to a Logistics Power Junction. Any other logistics pipe will not connect to a power junction. A single basic pipe is sufficient to power all other pipes connected physically via other pipes.

The central part of the pipe has a small square on each corner that will be red if the pipe is not receiving power from the network and green when powered. There are also colored lines on each end connected to an adjacent pipe or inventory. A red line indicates that there is no other logistics pipe in that direction, a red and green line means that there is another logistics pipe, but no power is received, and a full green line means that another logistics pipe is connected and powered. All other types of logistics pipes also have these indicators.

GUI:
Right-clicking with a Wrench opens the pipe's GUI. The top 9 slots in the GUI can be used to designate items to be routed into the adjacent inventory. The Default Route button defaults to "No" but if changed to "Yes" will allow any item entering the network without a destination to be routed to the adjacent inventory.

The Silver Lime Tree is crossbred from an Apple Oak Tree and a Silver Birch Tree. It can support Pomes, Nuts, and Prunes, but produces no natural fruit on its own. The Silver Lime has a higher Sappiness than Apple Oak and Silver Birch.

To complete this quest, you will need to shear off some leaf blocks from the tree using Shears. You will receive a purebred sapling as a reward.
The Fermenter breaks down organic materials into liquid Biomass. It is also used to create liquid Short Mead from some bee products.

The Mundane Larch Tree is crossbred from an Silver Birch Tree and a Red Spruce Tree. It does not support nor produce any fruit. The Mundane Larch has a higher Sappiness than Red Spruce and Silver Birch, and will grow as tall as the Red Spruce.

To complete this quest, you will need to shear off some leaf blocks from the tree using Shears. You will receive a purebred sapling as a reward.

Much like bees, trees can breed, cross-pollenate, and mutate. Only the Forestry versions of trees can do these, and by putting a vanilla sapling into a treealyzer will convert normal saplings into their Forestry variations.

Trees do not normally breed on their own. They need outside help, either from butterflies or from bees. As long as two trees are close to each other (but far enough away so their leaves don't conflict with each other), bees will (very slowly) carry pollen from one tree to another, fertilizing a random leaf block. This pollination is affected by the bee's Territory rating (better Territory means a larger area to work in) and Pollination rating (better Pollination means higher chance to pollenate). Even at maximum stats, the pollination efforts will be extremely slow, so focusing solely on breeding trees to the exclusion of everything else is not suggested.

Once a leaf block is pollenated, it will very subtlety change texture. While it is possible to see the difference, it's much easier to view it at a glance using the Spectacles. Once pollenated, you can use a Grafter on that leaf block to receive a crossbred sapling that might contain a combination of the two trees used in the crossbreeding. Depending on mutation rates and the combination of trees used, you might even get a new species of sapling.

Butterflies will naturally spawn around Forestry trees. These will allow you to breed trees without the use of bees, but they are extremely unpredictable. They will only pollenate leaves when they land on them.

You can pick up a butterfly by stunning it with a Right-click with a Scoop in hand. Once picked up, you can analyze it and/or drop it down directly onto a leaf block (with no guarantee that it will pollenate). When you drop a butterfly, it will remain stunned for a few seconds, but will eventually get back to flying again. Building a tall greenhouse-like structure is a good idea if you want to contain your butterflies around your trees.

Plant the Forestry versions of the Vanilla trees and shear off a stack of Leaf Blocks with Shears.

Ensure the leaves have the "Breedable" tooltip under the leaf block; otherwise, it is not the Forestry version.

Tired of trying to build out your base over long distances just to find the right climate for a bee to work in? The Acclimatizer is a machine that can modify a bee's Temperature and Humidity Tolerance.

To adjust a bee's climate tolerance, you will need to power the machine then place a Princess and a Drone in the left slot. Below this slot you can place up to three stacks of items used to modify the tolerance (see items below).

Note that items can be expended without anything happening. There's a low percentage chance of the tolerance actually changing, with diminishing returns at higher numbers. If you want a Temperature Tolerance of Up 5, expect to use a LOT of snowballs.

Interestingly, if you change a tolerance in the opposite direction of what the bee currently has, it will change to Both instead of Up or Down. A tolerance trait of Both is far more valuable than Up or Down. Humidity Tolerance more than 2 is wasteful, as there are only two humidity climate types.

Valid items for changing tolerance:
-Temperature Up: Lava Capsule, Lava Bucket, Blaze Powder, Blaze Rod
-Temperature Down: Ice, Snowball
-Humidity Up: Water Capsule, Water Bucket
-Humidity Down: Sand

The Alveary not only has no production penalty, but it has the ability to hold more frames than an Apiary. Each Frame Housing only holds one frame each, but as long as you replace any of the outside blocks on the lower two levels of the Alveary with Frame Housings, you can have up to 16 frames running at the same time. Frames in Frame Housings can be automated with pipes.

The Alveary Sieve is a very valuable addition to your Alveary if you plan on doing any extensive tree breeding in the near future. When placed on the lower two levels of an Alveary with Woven Silk placed inside, the Sieve will slowly gather up pollen from the nearby Forestry trees. This pollen can be used to speed up your cross-pollination efforts.

Repeatable - Instant
$25 to buy a Proven Frame that is used in an Apiary or Alveary to drastically increase production rate of Bees. The Frame does take damage over time.
A viaduct is a block that transfers players between configured locations.

All bees have specific requirements to work in. Two of these are temperature and humidity. All biomes have different values for these. A plains biome in is a comfortable temperate climate with Normal temperature and Normal humidity, perfect for bees that don't have any specific requirement, like the Forest Bee or the Meadows Bee.

If you try to put a Marshy Bee to work in a plains biome, they will refuse to work because they require Damp humidity and Normal temperature, found around rainforests, marshes, and swamps. Similarly, certain bees require Hellish temperature and Arid humidity, which can only be found in the Nether.

Until you can mutate your bees to be more tolerate of the biome you want to build your bees in, extend your base out until you find a biome that can support the bees you want to work with. You can see exactly what temperature and humidity the biome supports by placing down a Bee House or Apiary and then clicking on the climate button on the top right of the GUI.


Humidity and Temperature Tolerance is how well a bee can adjust to a climate that is not their favorite. This is a number scale ranging from -5 to +5 for both stats, and can work both ways for some bees.

If a bee has Normal/Normal for their temperature and humidity, and Up 1 for temperature tolerance and Down 1 for humidity tolerance, then the bee can work in Normal and Warm temperature climates and Normal and Arid humidity climates.

Temperature climates:
Icy, Cold, Normal, Warm, Hot/Hellish
§oNote: Hellish acts as Hot for the purposes of temperature. This is simply an indication that the bee uses the Nether biome.§r

Humidity climates:
Arid, Normal, Damp

betterquesting:10.name:8: Bee Info - Flowers, Territory, and Pollenation
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Most Bees require flowers to work. These flowers could range from normal Poppies to the weirder stuff like Smooth Stone. It all depends on the species of the bee.

Territory is the diameter around the housing in which the bee will seek out their chosen flower on an X/Y/Z axis. The most common rating is Average, which means the bee will look for their chosen flower within a 9x9x6 cube with the hive in the center. Alvearies have an innate ability to double the territory rating of a queen. If the bee species has a special effect, then the effect will work only within the bee's territory.

Pollination is a bee's ability to spread their flowers automatically, spawning new flowers or accelerating the growth of others. This effect depends on the chosen flower type of the bee. Bees which require normal flowers will spread those same flowers, while bees which favor cactus will accelerate the growth of nearby cacti. Other flowers may not even spread or be accelerated (e.g. Rocks). The range in which flowers can spread or are accelerated is triple that of the territory rating.

Valid flower types:
-Flowers: Minecraft flowers
-Jungle: Vine or fern
-Mushroom: Red or brown mushrooms
-Cacti: Cactus
-Wheat: Wheat
-Stone: Cobblestone, smooth stone, or stone brick
-Reeds: Sugar cane
-Redstone: Redstone ore or redstone block
-Nether: Nether Wart
-End: Chorus
-Books: Bookshelf
-Ore: Any ore block
-Snow: Minecraft flowers
-None: Does not require flowers

There are 3 types of basic frames: Untreated Frames, Impregnated Frames, and Proven Frames. The first two can be made by the player, but the Proven Frame may only be purchased from Villagers, quests, or other player's. These frames double the production rate of an Apiary per frame, no matter the type. The difference between frames is how long they will last while the Queen is working.

-Lifespan: modifies your queen's lifespan.

-Territory: modifies the bee's territory range.
-Genetic Decay: will modify how often an Ignoble Stock queen will die out.
-Mutation Chance: will modify the percentage chance a bee will mutate into a new species.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Bee Info - Lifespan, Fertility, and Speed
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Lifespan is how long a queen will live. Each lifespan has a set amount of cycles, and each cycle is 27.5 seconds long. A Normal lifespan will last 40 cycles, or 18 minutes 20 seconds, whereas a Shorter lifespan will last only 20 cycles, or 9 minutes 10 seconds.

Once each cycle is over with, the queen will produce their product based on the product's percentage chance. For example, if the queen will produce honeycomb at a 40 percent chance, then every 27.5 seconds there is a 40 percent chance to get a honeycomb.

When the lifecycle is over with, the queen will die and will produce one princess and a number of drones determined by the Fertility rating. Most queens will produce two drones, but there are some that produce up to four, and even some that only produce a single drone.

Speed is a bit of a misnomer. It doesn't actually speed up anything, rather it gives a bonus or penalty to the percentage chance of production. A speed rating of Normal gives no bonus or penalty, while a Faster rating gives a +40 percent increased chance, and a Slow rating gives a -20 percent penalty.

Bees with Short or worse lifespans are best for breeding up a lot of drones, while bees with Fast or better lifespans are best at producing goods. The Wintry Bee is extremely good at producing spare drones, having 4 Fertility and Short lifespan. Similarly, the Doctoral Bee has a Normal speed but Longest lifespan, making it a good workhorse.

Some bees have additional effects that they perform within range of their working territory. Some of these are beneficial effects that can help you, some... not so much.

A Queen will only perform her effect when working and when conditions are right. For example, the Beatific effect gives a small bit of regeneration, but only if the player is within range. The Creepers effect will randomly spawn creepers within the territory if the light level is low enough. The Water effect will fill up nearby tanks with water.

To protect yourself from negative effects that affect players, you will need to gird yourself in a full set of Apiarists Armor or just simply stay out of the bee's territory until the Queen dies off.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Bee Info - Dominant vs. Recessive Genes
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
When looking at a bee with the Beealyzer, you may notice that some traits are red and some traits are blue. Red are the Dominant genes, while blue are the Recessive genes. Dominant genes will more likely be chosen when breeding over Recessive genes. The "better" traits are more likely to be Recessive, making breeding them into a new bee without special help from machines a trial.

Let's use a Punnet Square with a Fast (Recessive) trait and a Slow (Dominant) for an example:

        Slow      |    Fast
------------------------------------
Slow |    S/S    |    S/F
Fast |    S/F     |    F/F

If all traits were Dominant or all were Recessive, then there would be a 25 percent chance of a purebred Slow/Slow, a 50 percent chance of a mixed Slow/Fast, and a 25 percent chance of a purebred Fast/Fast. But because Dominant genes are... well... dominant, they will be chosen over Recessive genes. In the above example, you're looking at a 75 percent of a Slow/Slow and only a 25 percent of a Fast/Fast.

When you put a bee into a Beealyzer, you will notice two columns. The first column are the Active traits. These are the traits that the bee currently uses. The Inactive traits have no effect on a bee except during crossbreeding. Purebred bees are bees in which both the Active and Inactive columns are the same.

If a Princess has a different trait in either the Active or Inactive column, then only the Active column will be used when the Princess turns into a Queen. The stats of Drone will not matter except for the purposes of crossbreeding when the Queen dies off. For example, a Meadows Princess with Slow speed as the Active trait and Fast speed as the Inactive breeds with a Rocky Drone with Normal speed as a purebred trait will produce a Meadows Queen that uses only the Slow speed trait when working. But when the Queen dies off, the resulting Princess and Drones may mutate into any of the three speeds in either Active or Inactive slots, and could potentially result in a Meadows bee with a Rocky Inactive or even a purebred Rocky.

When crossbreeding, there is an equal chance the resulting new bees will inherit traits from the Active and Inactive columns from the parents. A Princess with Fast/Slow and a Drone with Slowest/Normal will have a 25 percent chance of passing on any of these four to their children. A Fast/Fast and a Slow/Normal will have a 50 percent chance of passing on a Fast trait in either the Active or Inactive column and 25 percent for both Slow and Normal traits. This check is made for all children, resulting in a lot of mixed breed clutter if you are crossbreeding a lot of different traits together.

It takes a lot of patience and breeding to get a purebred bee with the traits you want. You cant selectively choose which traits will be put into a bee... yet...

Pollen, much like saplings, can be analyzed in your Treealyzer to see the tree stats.

Once you have pollen in hand, you can Right-click any non-pollenated Forestry leaf block to instantly pollenate it. The leaf block will now be ready to be broken with a Grafter. By using the pollen on an opposite tree in a mutation combination (for example, Apple Oak pollen on a Silver Birch leaf block), this leaf block will act as if both trees cross-pollenated and might produce a mutation or a simple crossbreed of traits.

Note: Any Forestry pollen will work for this quest.

Much like bees, trees have stats that effect what they do. When placed into a treealyzer, pollen or a sapling will reveal what stats it has. And much like bees again, they will have Active/Inactive and Dominant/Recessive genes.

The list of traits a tree can have are as followed:
§l-Species§r: This is the species of the tree itself.
§l-Saplings§r: How often you will get saplings when leaves are broken without a Grafter.
§l-Matures§r: How quickly a sapling will grow into a tree.
§l-Height§r: How tall a tree will grow from base to top, and will determine the number of leaf blocks a tree will have.
§l-Girth§r: How wide a tree will grow. Most trees are 1x1, but some can grow to 4x4 (requiring at least 16 saplings to grow).
§l-Yield§r: Like the Saplings trait, this determines how often the tree will give fruit.
§l-Sappiness§r: How much Biomass you will receive in a Fermenter.
§l-Soil§r: The favored biome the tree will grow in.
§l-Supports§r: Determines exactly what family of fruits the species will allow. There can be multiple values in this trait. Valid families: Pome, Prunes, Nuts, Jungle.
§l-Fruits§r: Tells you exactly what fruit the tree will produce.
§l-Family§r: Tells you what category that fruit is in.
The Precision Assembler is a multiblock machine used to create many Advanced Rocketry based electronics using RF.

Several multiblock machines in this mod make use of either Coils, Motors or both.

These come in several tiers, with the more expensive ones making the machine work faster, but any given machine will accept any of them.
The Cutting Machine is a multiblock machine that is used to cut silicon boules into wafers then into circuits.
The Crystallizer is a multiblock machine used to make various crystals using RF.

Titanium is not naturally found anywhere expect for space or in very small amounts in The Nether. However, you need Titanium to actually go to space... so, you are going to have to create some the hard way before you can start mining it off of astroids.

The Electrolyzer is a multiblock machine that uses RF to turn liquid Nitrogen into Hydrogen and Oxygen.

Both of those fluids are needed later on to make Rocket Fuel as well as to be able to breath in space with the Space Suit.
The Electrolyzer is a multiblock machine that uses RF to create Rocket Fuel from liquid fuel and liquid hydrogen.

The Gas Charge Pad can fill items with Hydrogen or Oxygen without using RF.

Simply pipe in the gas you want and insert any container that you want to insert the gas into.

Most importantly though, standing on top of it with either a Space Suit Chest-Piece or a chestplate enchanted with Airtight Seal equipped will fill it with Oxygen.

The Space Station Assembler is used to assemble Space Stations. You will need the same setup as for building Rockets, the only differences being Space Stations don't need fuel, and when they're built, they compress into item form.

The item then needs to be launched into space, with a rocket with a Satellite Bay. The rocket will be lost, unless you give it a Guidance Computer with the Space Station ID Chip in it, in which case it'll land on the newly made Space Station.

You can travel there by making a Rocket, and placing the Space Station ID Chip in the Guidance Computer.

§1It is important that you don't lose your Space Station ID Chip, once it has been set to your Space Station. If you lose the chip, and don't have any other means of transport to the Space Station, it is gone forever. Luckily, it can be copied in the Satellite Builder multiblock.

Satellites are objects you can build and launch into orbit using Satellite Bay on a rocket that can perform useful actions such as collect energy and data, or even be used to terraform a planet.

Satellites are built in the Satellite Builder. The machine will take components and a Satellite id chip and produce a satellite and a programmed Satellite id chip. Place the Satellite Builder on top of an Input Plug to get started.


§ohttp://arwiki.dmodoomsirius.me/AdvancedRocketry/items/satellite.php

The Astrobody Data Processor is a multiblock machine used to research Asteroids, when provided with information from satellites. Asteroids contain rare metals in abundance.


§ohttp://arwiki.dmodoomsirius.me/AdvancedRocketry/guides/Missions.php
The Oxygen Vent, when supplied with Oxygen and RF, will fill a large room it's in with Oxygen, given that it's airtight.
The Gravity Controller lets you control the gravity of your Space Station.

The CO2 Scrubber, with Carbon Collecting Cartridge in, will decrease the amount of oxygen the Oxygen Vent uses.

You can place up to 2 next to a Oxygen vent - the rotation of the CO2 Scrubber matters.

The Carbon Collecting Cartridges will be destroyed over time.

Building a Warp Core multiblock in your Space Station will allow you to travel to other planets and solar systems in a heartbeat. It uses Rupert Crystals as fuel.

The Warp Controller is used to set the destination of your Space Station.

Missions can be performed to collect Ore or harvest Gasses from Gas Giants and return them to your base. Missions can be monitored from a Rocket Monitoring Station. However, before a Rocket can mine an Asteroid or harvest Gasses, one has to be found with satellites collecting data.

Small Asteroid Mining can be used to gather Titanium and Rupert Ore.

Iridium Enriched Asteroid Mining is the only way to collect Iridium and Dimensional Shard Ore.
Before you launch yourself into space, you should ensure you have everything required to make the trip in the first place and make it there safely. I prepared a checklist of everything you need...
Add some meat to a drying rack and wait... After a few minutes, the food will age into a delicious jerky.

Oreberry Bushes are generated in the world around level 32. It grows a Oreberry which can be harvested and smelted into a nuggets. The Oreberry Bush has 3 stages of growth, it produces a berry in its final stage, but doesn't propagate. The Berry can be harvested by right-clicking on the bush when the Berry is visible. It may only be planted in light level 6 or below. The Oreberry Bush cannot be initially placed on top of another, but the block it is planted on may be removed and it will persist. 

The Essence Berry Bush bears Concentrated Essence Berry, which are eaten to gain XP points. The Essence Berry Bush may be cultivated for its Berry. It does not have light-level constraints, and grows at the same rate regardless of light level, although it does not propagate.

It is possible to use the Harvester from MineFactory Reloaded for harvesting.

Flashing §c§c§r§cred quests§r are unlocked, and you can click on them to see how to complete §rthem.

Completed quests flash §9§s§b§9blue§r§r if they have a reward that hasn't been collected, and are §agreen§r if they don't.

§8Gray quests §rhave not been unlocked and cannot be completed. You can hover over locked quests to see what quests they require to be completed to unlock them.

Lines are not the best way to see quest connections; the you do not need to complete all quests that are connected in a line in order. If the quest is §cred§r, it is unlocked, even if there's a §4red line§r connecting to them.
