Modular Storage is a great mid tier storage solution. It can hold hundreds of searchable items; however, it lacks the IO power of a full Applied Energistics system.

The Modular Storage block on its own does nothing, it needs to have a Storage Module inside of it to function. The first tier holds a maximum of 100 stacks, each tier adding another 100 stacks. With the Storage Module installed, the Modular Storage acts basically like a chest. Stacks do not automatically combine; if you put a stack of 32 Dirt and later another stack of 16, they will stay separate. Hit the Z button at the bottom of the GUI to combine the stacks. Above the Z button, you can change how the items are shown, be it a list, two columns, or stacks like most other inventories. The button directly to the right of that one changes the way the items are sorted (you can install a Generic Type Module to add more options). The G button will combine the items into groups depending on the way they are sorted.

The Remote Storage and its Module allow increased functionality. Place the Storage Module inside one of the spaces for it in the Remote Storage and place the other Module on the right of it, and it will bind them together. You can then place the RSM into a Module Storage (or even multiple of them) and it will access that Storage Module. You can even have multiple Storage Modules in a single Remote Storage, and so long as they all have an ID (they've been bound to any RSM), you can cycle between the Storage Modules by hitting the C at the bottom left of the Modular Storage GUI.

The Storage Scanner allows you to access all nearby inventories around itself remotely. Set the radius and hit the Scan button, and it will detect nearby inventories. Select an inventory from the list to access it. You can reorder the list using the buttons to the left of it. You can only insert items into inventories on the list that have the star enabled, and then you insert through the blue slot at the bottom left. It will enter the first acceptable inventory on the list, starting at the top. If you wish to specify which items go where, put filtered inventories at the top of the list. You can disable the star at the bottom left and it will instead insert items to whichever inventory is currently selected. You can select "All Routable" from the list and it will display every inventory with a star at once.
If you place a Manatide Bellows next to a Mana Pool, it will increase the mana output rate. If you place it next to a furnace, it will increase the efficiency of said furnace.

The Snowflake Pendant turns water source blocks into ice while the player is in the area.

The Pyroclast Pendant will extinguish fire from a player if they are not standing in a block that causes burns.

§oBoth of these pendants must be worn in the respective Baubles slot in order to function.§r
The Rod of the Terra Firma flatens land by adding or removing dirt to/from the area and uses a bit of mana per use.
The Rod of the Shifting Crust will replace blocks in a 7x7 area with another block. Shift-right-click on a block to select the block you want.

The Rod of the Plentiful Mantle uses mana to show nearby ores in a 15 block radius around the player by highlighted the ores for a short time with colored particles visible through walls. Every color shows a single type of ore, but is different on every use.

Wearing a full set of Manaweave Robes will increase the range to 20 blocks and decrease the mana cost by 35%.

§lAnd Throw it on The Ground!§r

When worn as a bauble, The Soujourner's Sash makes you run faster, jump higher (with step-assist), and fall from greater heights without taking damage.

The Drum of the Wild harvests tall grass, flowers, and crops in a 25x25x7 block area when supplied with a mana burst.

The Drum of the Canopy harvests leaves in a 24x24x7 block area when supplied with a mana burst. Leaves drop items as if a hand broke them.

The Drum of Gathering shears nearby sheep, fill buckets with milk (if the bucket is under a cow).

To give drums mana, you must use a mana pulse spreader or mana blaster. A regular mana spreader will not work.
The Charm of the Diva will cause hostile mobs to attack another enemy instead of you; however, there must be another enemy around to work.
When the entire Manasteel set is worn, mana cost on items and rods is reduced by 10 percent.

When the entire Terrasteel armor set is worn, you will receive the will of the ancients:
- Passive mana generation.
- Mana cost on tools and rods will decrease by 20 percent.
- Passive health regeneration when hunger bar is not full.
- All wills dropped by the Guardian of Gaia ON HARD MODE.

Each piece of armor gives an 11 percent chance to spawn an attack pixie after the player has been attacked.

When the entire Elementium armor set is worn, the player will receive the Great Fairy's Blessing:
- Decreases mana cost on tools and rods by 10 percent.
- Pixies near the player will get a random potion effect.
Some helmet armor pieces allow you to combine googles of revealing with that armor piece to combine both effects.

The Arcane Ear will emit a redstone pulse whenever a noteblock plays within hearing distance of it. It needs to be able to recognize the sound though, so you'll want to place it above the same block type the noteblock is on (if the noteblock is on a grass block, place the Arcane Ear on a grass block).

Arcane Alembics can only hold 32 of a single aspect at a time. You can empty them using glass phials by right-clicking on the Alembic. The phial can only hold 8 essentia at a time; No more; No less.

To upgrade your storage to something that can hold a bit more, you can place your newly collected phials into a Warded Jar. Warded Jars can hold 64 of each aspect and are used for many different crafting processes later down the road.

You can semi-automate the storage of essentia using Essentia Tubes. The research for Essentia Tubes is right below the Arcane Furnace. The pipes can be a bit of a task to manage though. You can't have two types of Essentia in the pipe at the same time. As a solution, you can make a valve. The valves stop the flow of essentia through a pipe system so you can control what is piped when and where.

The Essentia Crystallizer crystallizes liquid essentia into a crystallized item form. Each crystal of essentia can be distilled for 1 point of essentia in its aspect. The crystals can be stored in chests or other inventories more easily than liquid form, they will stack by aspect, and they can be counted out to distill any chosen amount of essentia.

To make crystallized essentia, you must pipe liquid Essentia into the crystallizer's input port. The crystallizer will begin to spin, and will eject the crystals from the front. Without power, the crystallizer works very slowly. Supplying the crystallizer with Terra centivis from an energized node will make it much faster.

Note: Any Crystallized Essentia type will work for this quest.

The Straw Golem is the most basic golem. While they may be squishy and weak, at least they are fast.
- Durability: Very Low
- Strength: Very Low
- Self-repair: Average
- Carry Limit: 1
- Speed: Fast
- Upgrades: 1

The golem you craft can be placed in the world, but will remain inactive until given an Animation Core. The placement of the golem needs to be considered carefully - if you wish it to interact with inventories, you will need to place it on the inventory on the side you wish it to interact with. Most golems can operate in a range of 16 blocks around their home location.

The Golemancer's Bell helps you instruct Golems (used with some Animation Cores)

§9Gather Animation Core§r
Picks up items within a 16 blocks area and places them in its home inventory. It does not use marks, but it does have item slots which can be used to restrict the items it looks for.

The Silverwood Golem is the most advanced golem available.

Books can only be crafted or found in the wild. Book creation requires liquid glue.

Liquid Glue is created by melting down horses in a smeltery. There needs to be a molten liquid in the smeltary for this to work.
Any Golem who walks over the Golem Fetter when it is powered with a redstone signal will stop what they are doing immediately and stand still. Unpower the Fetter to have the golems resume work.

§9Fill:§r
Needs to have one or more inventories marked to work with, and particular items specified to handle. The Golem will then watch the marked inventories for certain items to appear. It will then fetch the items and place them in their home inventory.

It has two modes of operation, "precise" and "any". In "any" mode, it will move items until the marked inventories run out of items, or the home inventory runs out of space. In "precise" mode, an amount is specified for each item. The golem will only go to fetch items if there are not already that many items in the home inventory.

§9Empty:§r
Golem will watch their home inventory for items, either all items or those specified by their item slots. If a suitable item is placed there, they will take it out and place it at a marked location. Their item slots can be used to make them only empty particular items. With the Order upgrade, they can also separate particular items into different locations or inventories.

§9Harvest:§r
Golem will harvest any recognized crop plant within a 4 block area (vertical works also). The Golem can go out of range to use stairs or other paths.

With the Order upgrade, Golems will attempt to replant ordinary crops, but they will do so with whatever seeds they find nearby after harvesting. In many cases, it may be more useful to let a Use golem handle replanting. Except for replanting, they will not pick up the harvested items, but will leave them where they fell. Harvest golems do not use inventories, marks, or item slots.

§9Guard:§r
Golem will seek out and attack hostile mobs. Guard golems do not use inventories, marks, or item slots. By default, they will not attack creepers. A number of accessories apply primarily to Guard golems:
- Armor and a Mace provide protection and increased damage.
- Dart launcher to attack creepers; however, they will not use it against flying mobs such as wisps.
- Visor lets their kills drop experience and perhaps some "player" drops.
- Order lets them be set to attack other targets as well, including peaceful mobs and other players.

§9Decanting:§r
Golem will collect liquid blocks from a marked pool and place them in its home inventory (which must be capable of accepting liquids). They have a single item slot which can only accept a full bucket. While they do not work very well with cauldrons or even crucibles, they are useful in connection with various industrial mods that offer "tanks" and piping systems for liquids. 

If instructed to carry entire liquid source blocks, they will carry the same amount of liquid as a bucket. Otherwise (taking from liquid tanks or such) they will only be able to carry 100 "millibuckets" (a tenth of a bucket) per item of "carrying capacity". That is, if, an Empty golem with the same body and upgrades would carry 2 items, the Decanting golem will carry only 200 millibuckets of liquid. With an Entropy upgrade, they can empty a pool from the far edge, instead of picking up the same block repeatedly. They cannot handle essentia.

§9Butcher:§r
Golem will attack only farm animal mobs. They will not attack babies, or the last two adults of any type within their range. They can be fitted with the Visor accessory to drop experience from their kills, or a Mace to speed the killing. Butcher golems do not use inventories, marks, or item slots.

§9Alchemy:§r
Golem is used to distribute essentia from a source (their home) to various destination jars or other containers. If they are placed on an Alchemical Furnace, they can take essentia from any alembic in the stack.  Their capacity is the same "carrying capacity" defined by their body and upgrades, but measured in points instead of items. They can only carry one aspect of essentia at a time.  They can also be placed on a essentia buffer (such as the output for a centrifuge) but may get confused in certain cases: specifically, if there are more than two aspects present, but none of them with enough of any to fill their carrying capacity. 

The Alchemy core's marks indicate either a device (such as a reservoir or buffer), or a bank of jars.  For each jar marked, they will "find" a group of jars which are directly (not diagonally) next to, above, or below each other, including the marked jar.  (It is wise to mark more than one jar in a row, in case some jars are removed and break up the group.)  If a device is marked, they will fill that device only, generally ignoring jars.  Otherwise, they will consider all the jars they know about, and will fill jars by a fixed priority:
- Labeled jar
- Unlabeled jar
- Warded jar
- Void jar
- Partly-filled jar
- New empty jar

§9Use:§r
Golem can right/left-click on marked locations, optionally with an item in hand. This lets them place blocks, plant crops, press switches, and use some tools on a marked space or block. They cannot mine blocks, nor can they interact with mobs.  If placed on an inventory, they will take items from that inventory to place or use, and item slots can restrict what items they can take out of the chest. However, they can also be placed on a non-inventory location, in which case they can only click with an empty hand. The checkboxes in their GUI specify whether they should left-click or right-click, whether they should be "sneaking", or whether they need to click on an existing block or an empty space.

§9Sorting:§r
Golem will move any items in its home inventory to any marked inventory, if the target inventory already contains at least one of that item. There is no way to limit the golem to particular items, or to specify items which are not in the marked chests. 

The Entropy upgrade allows treating items more "generically":
- Ignore NBT data
- Ignore metadata values
- Ignore specific ore dictionary

§9Fishing:§r
Golem will fish in any nearby water. It can catch fish, treasure, and junk that a player might catch with a fishing rod. Their fishing rod does not wear out. The fishing rate depends on the golem's strength. The items they catch will be strewn about the area, so a Gather golem will usually be needed to collect them. Fishing golems do not use inventories, marks, or item slots.

- Entropy: Decrease the junk rate.
- Ordo: Increase the treasure rate.
- Fire: Automatically cook fish.
- Air: may occasionally catch two items at once.

§9Chop:§r
Golem harvests trees, chopping them from the top down. Their range is similar to the Harvest golems, and will not gather the wood or saplings, nor can they replant trees. Their axe does not wear out. Chop golems do not use inventories, marks, or item slots. The speed of the woodcutting is determined by the strength of the golem.

§9Break:§r
Golem will break the marked blocks with the given tools.

- Order will choose the best tool to break the block.
- Entropy it will ignore metadata on tools.

§9Bodyguard:§r
Golem will follow the player and attack mobs which attack the player first.

§9Air:§r
Increases movement and ranged attack speed.

§9Earth:§r
Increases melee damage, harvesting speed, and carry limit (goes up by 4-16).

§9Fire:§r
Adds more interface slots, melee attacks set target on fire.

§9Water:§r
Increases activity range and range/accuracy for ranged attacks.

§9Order:§r
Allows use of colored markers, unlocks various features for different cores.

§9Entropy:§r
Adds Thorns effect. Can work more categorically with items, optionally ignoring metadata value, ignoring NBT data, and ore dictionary.

§9Top Hat:§r
Increases health.

§9Spectacles:§r
Increases vision range.

§9Bowtie:§r
Increases speed.

§9Fez:§r
Rapid healing.

§9Dart Launcher:§r
Gains a ranged attack. (Guard golem)

§9Visor:§r
Drop experience and player-only drops. Slight armor increase. (Guard or Butcher golem)

§9Iron Plating:§r
Heavy armor, slower movement.

§9Mace Arm:§r
Increases melee damage. (Guard or Butcher golem)

The Travelling Trunk is a chest that follows you around carrying its contents. It can teleport after you similarly to dogs and cats, and can even follow you between dimensions. It can be picked up with the Golemancer's Bell, but normally drops its contents when you do so. The trunks are sturdy but not invulnerable. If damaged, they can be healed quickly by feeding them, or slowly on its own.

Trunks can accept one of the elemental upgrades used for golems:
- Air: Moves faster.
- Earth: More item slots.
- Fire: Attacks hostile mobs, setting them on fire.
- Water: Nearly invulnerable. In SMP, can only be used by the player who placed it.
- Entropy: Sucks in loose items nearby (if it has room for them).
- Order: Can be picked up with its contents, as an item.

The Paving Stone of Travel encourages players to walk on it by granting them faster speed when they walk on it.

The Paving Stone of Warding prevents most mobs from walking into the block.

The Infernal Furnace acts like a normal furnace; however, it never needs any fuel and can sometimes double the output. Find the multiblock setup diagram in your Thaumonomicon under the Artifice tab. To complete the multiblock structure, right-click it with your wand. Make sure it has at least 50 Ignis and 50 Terra in it. The input is at the top where the hole is, and the output pops out of the iron bar.

You can upgrade the Infernal Furnace by piping in Ignis from a jar into one of the holes on the side. You can also add up to 2 arcane bellows to the other two holes to increase yeild, increase speed, and decrease warp effect.

The Lamp of Growth speeds up crop growth. It requires Herba essentia, which must be provided by a pipe. When placing the lamp, you have to put the pipe first and then attach the lamp to it. The amount of essentia used depends on the number of eligible plants within range. It affects all growable plants (crops, saplings, etc.) in a circular 12 block area. The effect can pass through solid blocks. The effects of multiple lamps stack.

The Lamp of Fertility speeds up breeding of animals. Any breedable animal within range will periodically go into "love mode", without need for food and regardless of whether it has bred recently. Generally this will happen to two animals at a time, but to successfully breed, they still need to meet some of the usual conditions: In particular, they must be able to reach each other, and both must have solid footing. A species will not be fertilized if there are already 8 or more of them within range. The lamp requires Victus essentia to work, which must be piped to the lamp. It will use more Victus according to the number of animals it puts into love mode, regardless of whether they breed successfully.

§oRemember: Only YOU can prevent zombie outbreaks.§r

The arcane lamp creates additional light sources which acts like a Torch in a sphere with a radius of 16 blocks centered on it. This will include caves or other areas behind walls. One downside, it might put a light where one isn't wanted, like inside a darkroom.

When attached to the base of an arcane bore, the arcane lamp will light up the tunnel that the bore digs.

Magic Mirrors allow you to transport items between two places. By placing one mirror on a wall, and right-clicking it with another mirror in your hand, will link both mirrors together. Then place the other mirror on another wall. Throw an item in the mirror to transport it (it works both ways).

Hand Mirrors allow you to transport items to a linked magic mirror, no matter where you are. Link the hand mirror by right-clicking it on a Magic Mirror. You cannot pull items out of the hand mirror.

Essentia Mirrors transport essentia instead of items, but cannot work with essentia pipes.

The Node Stabilizer must be placed under a node to take effect. It will stop the node from draining vis from other nodes and stops other nodes from draining from it while also preventing unstable nodes from losing their vis, has a tiny chance to eventually remove the unstable debuff completely and has an unrealistically small chance of turning fading nodes into pale nodes.

The downside to the node stabilizer is that it makes the node it affects recharge vis at half its normal rate. Applying a redstone signal to the stabilizer will turn it off.


The Advanced Node Stabilizer acts like a normal node stabilizer but with key differences. It will still stop the node it affects from being drained but the node can now drain from other lesser nodes. It also has a higher chance to improve fading and unstable nodes.

The downside is that any nodes it affects will have their recharge rates effectively reduced to nothing. They will recharge at an extravagantly reduced rate.

Feed RF into the bottom middle of the Launch Pad to supply it with power. Connect the Control Panel to the front and the Support Frame to the back of the Launch Pad. With the Location Linker in hand, right-click a location in the world where the missile should fire at. Then, shift+right-click the Control Panel to link it to that location.

Supply the Launch Pad with a missile and click "Launch" in the GUI to launch a missile. Note: Both the launcher and target location must both be chunkloaded to work properly; however, the path the missile will take does not need to be chunkloaded.

Missile Factory:
-Top Slot: Explosive type for the missile.
-Middle Slot: Circuit to control accuracy of the missile.
-Bottom Slot: Fuel Canister to control the distance and speed of the missile.
-Right Slot: Plating to control how protected the missile is from Anti-Missile Turrets.


§cNote: Any missile will work for this quest.§r
The Anti Missile Turret, when supplied with Bullets and a large amount of power, will shoot bullets once every 0.5 seconds at any missiles within its range.
The Sentry Turret, when supplied with Bullets and a large amount of power, will shoot bullets once every 0.5 seconds at any mobs
§9Take that USSR!§r

Build a large Banana Tree farm on a Space Station.

- Must have at least 256 Banana Trees.
- Must be built on a Space Station that is equipt for long-term living.
- Must be fully automatic and capable of running indefinitely without ANY player intervention.

Create a secret Soviet missile silo deep under the ocean.

- Must have at least 4 different Missile launch pads ready to be launched within seconds.

The Ethereal Bloom shows a strong resistance to Taint, and will clear a small area around them from this vile corruption. They cannot cleanse the area directly around taint nodes; however, they do reverse the effect of sinister nodes after the node has been removed.

The Flux Scrubber is used to clean areas of Flux. When powered with Aer vis from an energized node, it will slowly clean up any taint within 16 blocks while also providing a bit of Praecantatio essentia from the Flux it cleans in the process. It can only hold a little bit of essentia so it must be continually emptied or drained as it will keep working even if full.

The Arcane Spa will pump any liquid within onto the block that it is facing, either on itself or adjacent. To stop it pumping, you can apply a redstone signal. The gui allows you to choose whether to just pump the liquid put into it immediately or mix it first. The only mixing combination available so far is bath salts and water. This produces Purifying Liquid, which protects a character from Warp effects. To fill the Spa, right-click on it with a water bucket.
I can clean it now, but what is taint? Perhaps I need it? Perhaps it needs me...

Hopper:
- Useful for early game automation.
- Can be placed under chests or machines to pull out items.
- Can suck up items that fall on them.
- Used in many redstone builds.

Hopper Ducts:
- Can send items into inventories above them.
- Won't pull items from inventories above them.
- Only have a single inventory slot.
- Can be pointed in a different direction after placing them by hitting them with a stick.
- Have smaller hitboxes, making it easier to reach blocks behind them.

§aItemSink Module:§r
Tells your LP system "I'll take all of x item that isn't going anywhere and put it in my storage". It won't pull the items that are already being actively requested somewhere else in the system (i.e. for auto crafting, or supplying machines). It will only pull for items that don't already have somewhere to go.

In the "Requested items" list is where we can specify up to 9 different items for this pipe to ItemSink for. If we leave it blank, the pipe will provide no additional functionality over that of a Basic Logistics Pipe, so you should specify something in here.

You'll also see the option to make this a "default route". A default route is the lowest priority destination for items to go. This setting is useful if you want to have a miscellaneous chest or "items waiting to be setup for sorting" chest. You can either specify a default route for particular items, or you can leave it blank to let it be a default route for everything.

§aPolymorphic ItemSink Module:§r
Will always be configured to ItemSink to whatever items are currently in the storage that it is attached to. This is the most useful module for "miscellaneous" type chests.

§aModID ItemSink Module:§r
ItemSink for items per ModID. To configure it, drag any item from a mod into its interface and it will recognize the mod that item belongs to, which then allows you to add the mod to the list of things to ItemSink for. You can have multiple mods on a single pipe. You can also ItemSink for Vanilla Minecraft.

Take note that mods which have multiple "compartments" to them will need to be added for each of their compartments. For example, Buildcraft has BC Factory, BC Builders, BC Silicon, BC Transport, and BC Energy - all of which are recognized as separate mods to this module. It also has a lower priority than other ItemSinks.

§aOreDict ItemSink Module:§r
Will ItemSink for all the items/blocks that are in the same Ore Dictionary. So if you set it up for Wood Planks, any Plank from any mod will be allowed.

§aCreativeTab ItemSink Module:§r
Will ItemSink for all the items/blocks that are in the same CreativeTab. This may be useful in some cases instead of using ModID. However, you will have to view the CreativeTabs from the "Item Subsets" list in NEI.

§aAspect ItemSink:§r
Will ItemSink any items/blocks which has the particular Thaumcraft aspect(s) which are specified.

§aEnchantment ItemSink:§r
Will ItemSink any items/blocks which has the particular enchantment(s) which are specified.

The Provider Logistics Pipe can provide the contents of adjacent inventories to the connected logistics network, allowing other pipes to access and request them.

The Provider Logistics Pipe can be upgraded to a Provider Logistics Pipe Mk2 which operates much faster.

GUI:
The pipe's GUI can be accessed by right-clicking it with a Wrench. It has nine slots that can whitelist/blacklist items, and two buttons. If no items are added to the filter, all items will be provided.

The second button controls the providing mode. The following modes are available:
- Normal: Provides all items in connected inventories.
- Leave first stack: Provides all items except the first stack of each inventory. Note that this makes it impossible to provide items from single-slot inventories.
- Leave first and last stack: Provides all items except the first and last stacks of each inventory. Note that this makes it impossible to provide items from single-slot inventories and two-slot inventories.
- Leave 1 item per stack: Provides all items but one of each stack. Note that this makes it impossible to provide unstackable items.
- Leave 1 item per type: Provides all items but one of each type. Note that this makes it impossible to provide unstackable items from one-stack inventories.

§aCrafting Logistics Pipe:§r
Used to automate crafting within the logistics pipes network. It can be programmed to input items into an attached inventory through its GUI. It can also use Satellite Logistics Pipes which can be used to route items to remote destinations for a more complicated process, such as supplying Coal to a Furnace.

For normal crafting, a Logistics Crafting Table should be used as it provides several advantages over a traditional Crafting Table such as: using ghost items, 18 slot buffer inventory and instantaneous crafting.

§aCrafting Logistics Pipe Mk2:§r
Upgraded version of the Crafting Logistics Pipe. Has the capability of crafting up to 16 items at a time.

§aCrafting Logistics Pipe Mk3:§r
Upgraded version of the Crafting Logistics Pipe Mk2. Has the capability of crafting up to 16 items at a time and has an internal buffer.

§aSatellite Logistics Pipe:§r
Used with a Crafting Logistics Pipe to provide a remote destination for items in a crafting recipe. The pipe can be configured using a wrench where an ID can be set which must corespond to the ID set in the Crafting Logistics Pipe.

A common example of this pipe in use is for smelting items in a Furnace. The Crafting Logistics Pipe would be placed on the top of the Furnace with the Satellite Logistics Pipe on the bottom. The Charcoal would be routed to the bottom for every item that needed to be smelted once the Crafting Logistics Pipe was configured with Charcoal in one of the three right slots.
No Description

The Remote Orderer Logistics Pipe allows you access your network wirelessly in conjunction with a Remote Orderer. When an item is ordered with the Remote Order, the requested items will go to the pipe, where it will be placed in an adjacent inventory or on the ground. This, in conjunction with EnderStorage Ender Chests and Ender Pouches will allow you to access, insert, and remove items from your network from anywhere.

Once placed, right-click the pipe with a Remote Orderer to link the Orderer to it, and place an inventory like a chest right next to it. Now, when you request an item from the Remote Order, the requested items will be put into the chest for use.

§oNote: Any color for the Remote Orderer will work.§r

§aRequest Logistics Pipe:§r
Allows players to request items provided by the LP network. To use the pipe, right-click on it with a wrench, and a GUI will open. If it is connected to a chest or other storage, items requested will be inserted to the chest. Otherwise, they will drop from the pipe.

0 of an item means that none of that item are in the network but that item can be crafted. The GUI can also be filtered to show only craftable items, only stored items or both.

Another function this pipe has is to connect Logistics Pipes networks to Applied Energistics networks. If an ME Interface is connected to a request pipe, the ME network will be able to ‘see’ and order any materials from the LP network.

§aRequest Logistics Pipe Mk2:§r
Just like the Request Logistics Pipe; however, is usable without a wrench and shows Thaumcraft aspects.

-

§aSupplier Logistics Pipe:§r
Keeps a connected inventory supplied with the items specified in its GUI from the Logistics Pipes network.

§aActive Supplier Module:§r
Works the same as a Supplier Logistics Pipe.

§aPassive Supplier Module:§r
Works the same as a Supplier Logistics Pipe; however, it will not actively request items from the network. It will simply act as a high-priority destination for items that are traveling in the network.

Logistics Chassis Pipes allows a wide array of Modules can be installed to perform different functions within the logistics pipe network. Each different level of Logistics Chassis provides different numbers of slots.

- Mk1: provides 1 module slot.
- Mk2: provides 2 module slots.
- Mk3: provides 3 module slots.
- Mk4: provides 4 module slots.
- Mk5: provides 8 module slots.

§aLogistics System Entrance Pipe:§r
Items that pass through a Logistics System Entrance Pipe will be routed to the corresponding Logistics System Destination Pipe if they don't already have a destination. The default route counts as a destination so this only works if this is the first logistics pipe they pass through.

§aLogistics System Destination Pipe:§r
Where items that pass through a Logistics System Entrance Pipe are routed if they don't already have a destination. The default route counts as a destination so this only works if the entrance pipe is the first logistics pipe they pass through.


Logistics System Entrance Pipes and Logistics System Destination Pipes can be linked using a Logistics Item Card. Multiple pairs of entrance and destination pipes can exist on the same network.

A Logistics Firewall Pipe is used to restrict the connections between different logistics pipe networks. This can be used to create separate logistics pipe networks for different tasks and restrict how they interact. It must be configured with a Wrench.

The Logistics Firewall Pipe can restrict:
- Specific items from passing through
- All item except for selected ones from passing through
- Item requests
- Autocrafting recipes
- Sorting destinations
- Power

A Logistics Inventory System Connector is used to connect two separate logistics pipe networks together through a common inventory. The two connectors must be linked using a Logistics Item Card. Once this is complete, the two networks will behave as one network.

A common use of this system is using an Ender Chest as the linking inventory which allows the networks to be far apart or even in different dimensions.

Infernal Mobs are rare mobs with special abilities that are often much more difficult to kill than your average mob. Some abilities can make fighting the affected mobs tedious or even dangerous when added together, such as Bulwark and Regen or Wither and Vengeance. Note: Infernal mobs can spawn from anything: Natural spawns, spawn eggs, spawners, soul shards, etc.

Three Types of Infernal Mobs:
- Rare: 2-4 effects, 2-4x the base health.
- Ultra: 7 effects, 7x the base health.
- Infernal: 10-11 effects, 10-11x base health.

Possible Special Abilities:
- 1UP: Mob heals fully, one time, upon getting low on health.
- Alchemist: Throws random potions at the player.
- Berserk: Mob deals double damage; Hurts itself upon attacking the player.
- Bulwark: Mob has 50% damage resistance.
- Cloaking: Invisibility potion effect on the Mob.
- Ender: Can teleport to dodge attacks, reflecting damage on the player.
- Exhaust: Exhaust potion effect on the player.
- Fiery: Sets the Player on Fire, immune to fire-damage.
- Gravity: Knocks back or pulls the players.
- Lifesteal: Heals from successful attacks.
- Poisonous: Poison potion effect on the player.
- Quicksand: Slowness potion effect on the player.
- Regen: Heals 2 health per second.
- Sapper: Hunger potion effect on the player.
- Sprint: High movement speed bursts.
- Sticky: Has a chance to cause the player to drop the item they attack with.
- Twin: Comes back at full health after dying.
- Undying: Has a chance to respawn with full health.
- Vengeance: Reflects a portion of all damage done.
- Weakness: Weakness potion effect on the payer.
- Webber: Spawns a cobweb at the player's feet, immobilizing the player.
- Wither: Wither potion effect to the player.

The Town Mod is a protection system mod for heavily modded minecraft. The Mod is designed to allow chunks to be protected by other players from various game mechanics.

§d/town new <TownName>§r to create a new town. This costs $1,000 One Dollar Bills from the player's inventory.

Once you have claimed your first initial chunk of land, all other purchases for that town will be from within the town's bank. Access the bank with §d/town bank withdraw/deposit/info§r to move money back and forth between the bank and the player's inventory and to view the available funds.

§d/town claim§r to add the chunk you are in to your town. This costs $100 from the town's bank for each chunk purchased. §d/town overclaim§r to remove the chunk from your town.

§d/town setspawn§r to set the spawnpoint of your town. §d/town spawn§r to teleport to the town's spawnpoint. Teleporting costs $10 each time. Take some money out of the bank before teleporting.

§d/town invite <Player>§r to invite a player to your town. §d/town kick <Player>§r to remove a player from your town.

§d/town borders <show|hide>§r will display fake Gold Blocks around the borders of your land to make it easy to see what is your land.




§cPlease keep all town names in the format "TownName" with each world being capitalized without any numbers, special characters or spaces. This will keep everything formatted nicely on the server.

You may have to wait until the server restarts once after you create your town (for it to get written to disk) before you can start buying more land.§r

    -This also includes Mic-Spamming, voice modifiers, and ear-rape in voice channels.

§a3. No Soliciting:§r
    -Do not post links advertising you, another person, a discord server, etc. without approval from a Staff Member.

§a4. No Duping:§r
    -Duping is: A bug where an item, block, or entity is unintendedly duplicated.
    -This severely disrupts the server's economy and you will be permanently banned if you knowingly use it.
    -Please report all found dupe bugs to a staff member directly.
    -Avoid making a github issue for a found dupe issues.

§a5. Warfare:§r
    -Warfare between players or factions is only allowed if both sides agree and have it in writing somewhere on the server or on discord.
    -Do not kill or launch missiles at innocent players unless you are in mutual combat with them.
    -Both players must agree that they are enemies and are allowed to have large scale combat with each other.
    -Both players must agree on what property is off limits from destruction.
    -SpawnTown is off limits to warfare except in businesses that combat is required (such as a gladiator arena).

§a6. External Modification:§r
    -Do not add, alter, or remove any mods, plugins, hacks, or configuration files without first asking a staff member.
    -No external mods that give you an advantage over other players (This includes x-ray).
    -Hacks are never allowed and really take away the fun from everyone in the server.
    -If you wish to cheat, go to singleplayer.

§a7. Bugs/Problems:§r
    -The main goal is to provide a fun and fair experience for everyone. If you believe something is broken or you lost your items in an unfair way, contact a staff member and explain (in detail) what happened.
    -Please note: no items will be refunded due to negligence, ignorance, or not reading the already reported bugs or disclaimers.

§a8. Laggy Builds:§r
    -Any builds that add unnecessary or intentional lag to the server will be removed without refund.
    -You may ask a moderator to profile a build that you suspect may have performance issues.
    -Always add on/off switches to large builds. 

§a9. Wilderness:§r
    The Wilderness is classified as any area outside of player owned land. The below rules only apply to the wilderness (regardless of world dimension).
    -No death traps or places where other users will definitely die or get unreasonably stuck in.
    -No quarries in the Overworld outside of your protected land.
    -No unnecessary animal killing or land destruction. Please keep the wilderness beautiful.
    -Do NOT destroy or unreasonably modify "public infrastructure" (Minecart tracks, SpawnTown, etc.).
    -Do NOT destroy Thaumcraft's Nodes that are in the wilderness.

§a10. Player Data Corruption Protection:§r
    -Do not nest different storage containers inside of each other. (eg Backpacks inside of other backpacks, AE item cells inside of a chest).
    -In Minecraft if an item's NBT data gets too large, it will kick the player from the server instantly. The only way to solve this is to delete the player's data.
    -If this happens, your inventory will be reset without refund.

§a11. General Things to Avoid:§r
    -Sometimes "vanilla-like" furnaces can lag if there are items to process sitting in it, so try to process items without letting leftover in it.
    -Avoid leaving items on the ground uncollected, especially if you chunkload a farm.
    -Do NOT use AE2 storage buses on drawer controllers. In general, try avoiding drawer controllers all together, they are very laggy.
    -Do NOT place a motion sensor from OpenComputer in the world, it will crash the server.
    -Avoid fast input/output if you use ExtraCells, this is a known laggy mod.
    -Use fluid AE at your very own risk. It's known to be laggy, and lag-free alternatives do exist.
    -If lag from fluid AE is observed, staff will ask you to remove your fluid AE setups.
 
§a12. Un-escapable Traps:§r
    -Players must have a reasonable chance to escape an area by climbing, flying, etc.
    -Death pits are allowed as long as no protected block entraps the player once they enter it.
    -If a player dies in your base, their items still belong to them. You may not collect the items for yourself.
    -This rule is meant to protect your base and players that want to come check out your base.
    -Any traps that violate this will be removed without refund.

§a13. Discord Chat:§r
    -Please use the discord channels for their intended purposes.
    -Straying for a few messages is ok, but please move to the proper channel for longer conversations.
    -Do not excessively clutter channels with unwanted images, spam, or solicitation.

§a14. Language:§r
    -This server and discord is English only.
    -Players are free to use other languages in private DMs or private voice channels.

§a15. Punishments:§r
    -Punishments will usually be given from a formal written warning to a permanent ban depending on severity.
    -Bans are usually permanent unless it was a reasonable misunderstanding.
    -Don't be a statistic and attempt to test the rules.
    -Generally, you have an opportunity to appeal the ban by messaging TheOnlyRupert on discord in a private message.

§a16. Rule Disclaimer:§r
    -Staff reserves the right to modify the rules at any time without notice.
    -Staff members can deal with any situation at their own discretion.
    -If you have an issue with the application of the rules please take it up with TheOnlyRupert on discord in a private message.

§a17. Auto Clickers:§r
    -The use of any auto-mouse-clicking program and/or auto-keyboard-press program in the following situations:
    -Allowed: Auto kill mobs or animals in a mob farm (afk farming).
    -Allowed: Automating the usage of tile entities (such as the AE2 Grinder).

    -NOT Allowed: Anything else that would give you and unfair advantage over other players.
    -NOT Allowed: Using any cheats/hacks (such as kill-aura). This will get you permanently banned.
